249  /** 
250  @class MVMapView is the main entry class for all map operations inside the
251  web browser. It defines a JavaScript map client instance that fetches and 
252  displays map tile image tiles and features of interest(FOIs) fetched from 
253  the server side, and controls map related client side user interaction. </p>
254 
255  <p>All map content displayed by the map client is placed inside an HTML DIV 
256  element, which defines a rectangular area in the web page that displays the map.
257  The DIV element must be defined in the same HTML page where the map client instance
258  is created. Its size and position can be customized to meet the application's 
259  needs.</p>
260 
261  <p>When the application script invokes appropriate MVMapView methods and other 
262  client API, map content is displayed inside the map container DIV. The map 
263  client can display 5 different types of map content: map tiles, 
264  theme-based FOI, user-defined FOI, information window and map decoration.</p>
265  
266  <ul>
267  <li>
268    <p>Map tiles</p>
269    <p>A typical Oracle Maps application has at least one map tile layer, which 
270  assembles and displays pregenerated map image tiles from the map tile server.<p>
271    <p>A map tile layer can be added to the map client instance by invoking function
272    MVMapView.addMapTileLayer.</p>
273  </li>
274  <li>
275    <p>Theme-Based FOI</p>
276    <p>The application can display one or more theme-based FOI layers. Each theme-based FOI 
277    layer consists of a collection of interactive FOIs that meet certain query 
278    criteria defined in a MapViewer predefined theme. 
279    <p>A theme-based FOI layer can be added to the map client instance by invoking
280    function MVMapView.addThemeBasedFOI.</p>
281  </li>
282  <li>
283    <p>User-Defined FOI</p>
284    <p>The application can display one or more user-defined FOIs. A user defined FOI 
285    is a dynamic feature created by the application on the fly. When creating a 
286    user defined FOI, the application has to supply all feature attributes including
287    the geometry representation and rendering style. This is different from how 
288    the theme based FOI layer is created on the client side. When creating a theme 
289    based FOI layer, the application only needs to specify the name of the predefined theme. All 
290    feature attributes(spatial or non-spatial) are stored inside the database.</p>
291    <p>A user-defined FOI can be added to the map client instance by invoking
292    function MVMapView.addFOI.</p>
293  </li>
294  <li>
295    <p>Information window</p>
296    <p>An information window is a small pop-up window that displays customizable 
297    content in the map. 
298    <p>An Information window can be displayed by invoking function 
299    MVMapView.displayInfoWindow.</p>
300  </li>
301  <li>
302    <p>Fixed figures</p>
303    <p>Fixed figures are immovable elements such as copyright notes, scale bar, 
304    navigation panel and user defined map decoration features. A user defined 
305    map decoration feature is an application defined element that can contain any 
306    custom HTML content, for example, a map title or a custom control button.  
307    Fixed figures are displayed on top of everything else and is not moved when 
308    the user drags the map.
309  </li>
310  </ul>
311 
312  <p>Besides displaying the above map content, the application can easily 
313  plug in various build-in utilities as needed. 
314  Currently supported built-in utilities include: scale bar,
315  navigation tool bar, copyright panel, redlining tool, rectangle tool, marquee
316  zoom tool, overview map, etc. The application can access the a built-in utility 
317  by invoking the corresponding MVMapView function. For example, 
318  method MVMapView.addScaleBar adds a scale bar to the map.</p>
319  
320  <p>MVMapView also implements various functions that are essential for map application development. 
321  Application can use these functions to: get or change the map center and zoom level,  
322  change map client behavior by defining custom event handler for certain events, 
323  remove previously added map content, etc. </p>
324  
325  @param {Object} mapDiv the HTML DIV element where all map content is displayed.
326  @param {string} mapViewerBaseURL the base URL of the MapViewer server from which
327                  the map client fetches map tiles and FOI data. The typical MapViewer
328                  base URL is http://hostname:port/mapviewer. 
329  @constructor
330  */

735      this.base_div.style.zIndex = 70;*/

737    this.div.style.position = "absolute";

739    /*

741    {
742      this.div.style.width = MVUtil.pixel(this.getPaneWidth());
743      this.div.style.height =MVUtil.pixel(this.getPaneHeight());
744    }
745    else
746    {
747      this.div.style.width = "100%";
748      this.div.style.height = "100%";     
749    }*/
750    this.div.style.zIndex = 80;
751    this.div.style.left = MVUtil.pixel(0);
752    this.div.style.top  = MVUtil.pixel(0);
753    this.info_div.style.left = MVUtil.pixel(0);
754    this.info_div.style.top  = MVUtil.pixel(0);
755    this.divLeft = 0;
756    this.divTop =  0;   
757    this.origLeft = this.divLeft;
758    this.origTop = this.divTop;

775  /**
776  @private
777  */
778  MVMapView.prototype.setDragOffset = function(mouseX, mouseY)
779  {
780    this.dragOffsetX = mouseX-this.divLeft;
781    this.dragOffsetY = mouseY-this.divTop;
782  }
783  /**
784  @private
785  */
786  MVMapView.prototype.move = function(mouseX, mouseY)
787  {
788    this.reCenterTag = true;
789    this.divLeft = mouseX - this.dragOffsetX ;
790    this.divTop = mouseY - this.dragOffsetY ;
791    this.origLeft = MVUtil.getLeft(this.div);
792    this.origTop  = MVUtil.getTop(this.div); 
793    
794    var leftTop = this.checkMapDivLeftTop(this.origLeft, this.divLeft, this.origTop, this.divTop);
795    this.divLeft = leftTop.left ;
796    this.divTop = leftTop.top ;
797    
798    var newCenterX = this.mapCenterX + (this.origLeft-this.divLeft)/this.pixPerX ;
799    var newCenterY = this.mapCenterY - (this.origTop - this.divTop)/this.pixPerY ;
800    this.moveExternalAPITileLayers(this.divLeft-this.origLeft, this.divTop-this.origTop, 
801                                   newCenterX, newCenterY); 
802    var x = this.mapCenterX;
803    var y = this.mapCenterY;   
804    this.mapCenterX = newCenterX ;
805    this.mapCenterY = newCenterY ;
806    
807    if (x != this.mapCenterX || y != this.mapCenterY)
808    {
809      this.scrolled = true;   
810    }
811    MVUtil.setLeftTop(this.div, this.divLeft, this.divTop);
812    MVUtil.setLeftTop(this.info_div, this.divLeft, this.divTop);
813  } 
814  /**
815  *@private
816  *This method is deprecated. Please use {@link #setEventListener} instead.
817  @deprecated
818  */
819  MVMapView.prototype.addEventListener=function(eventType, listener)
820  {
821    this.setEventListener(eventType, listener) ;
822  }
823  /**
824  *This method is deprecated. Please use {@link #attachEventListener} instead.
825  @deprecated
826  */
827  MVMapView.prototype.setEventListener=function(eventType, listener)
828  {
829    if (eventType==MVEvent.RECENTER)
830    {
831      this.recenterListener=listener;
832    }
833    else if (eventType==MVEvent.MOUSE_CLICK)
834    {
835      this.mouseclickListener=listener;
836    }
837    else if (eventType==MVEvent.MOUSE_RIGHT_CLICK)
838    {
839      this.rightclickListener=listener;
840    }
841    else if (eventType==MVEvent.ZOOM_LEVEL_CHANGE)
842    {
843      this.zoomListener=listener;
844    }
845    else if (eventType==MVEvent.BEFORE_ZOOM_LEVEL_CHANGE)
846    {
847      this.beforeZoomListener=listener;
848    }
849    else if (eventType==MVEvent.MOUSE_DOUBLE_CLICK)
850    {
851      this.dblclickListener = listener;
852    }
853    else if (eventType==MVEvent.INITIALIZE)
854    {
855      this.initializeListener = listener;
856    }
857  }
858  
859  /**
860  *This method attaches an event listener function that is invoked when the specified map event occurs. 
861  *The event can be of the following types: MVEvent.RECENTER, MVEvent.MOUSE_CLICK,
862  *MVEvent.MOUSE_RIGHT_CLICK, MVEvent.MOUSE_DOUBLE_CLICK, MVEvent.ZOOM_LEVEL_CHANGE, MVEvent.BEFORE_ZOOM_LEVEL_CHANGE and MVEvent.INITIALIZE.
863  *<ul>
864  *<li>A MVEvent.RECENTER event occurs when the center of the map is changed, which 
865       can happen when the user drags the map or uses the navigation panel to pan the map. 
866       No parameter is passed to the MVEvent.RECENTER listener when it is invoked.</li>
867  *<li>A MVEvent.MOUSE_CLICK event occurs when the user clicks mouse left key on the map.
868       The mouse event object is passed to the MVEvent.MOUSE_CLICK listener when it is invoked.</li>
869  *<li>A MVEvent.MOUSE_RIGHT_CLICK event occurs when the user clicks mouse right key 
870       on the map. The mouse event object is passed to the MVEvent.MOUSE_RIGHT_CLICK listener when it is invoked.</li>
871  *<li>A MVEvent.MOUSE_DOUBLE_CLICK event occurs when the user double clicks mouse left key 
872       on the map. The mouse event object is passed to the MVEvent.MOUSE_DOUBLE_CLICK listener when it is invoked.</li>
873  *<li>A MVEvent.MOUSE_DOWN event occurs when the user press down the mouse left key on the map.
874       The mouse event object is passed to the MVEvent.MOUSE_DOWN listener when it is invoked.</li>
875  *<li>A MVEvent.MOUSE_UP event occurs when the user release the mouse left key after pressing it on the map.
876       The mouse event object is passed to the MVEvent.MOUSE_UP listener when it is invoked.</li>
877  *<li>A MVEvent.ZOOM_LEVEL_CHANGE event occurs after the map zoom level is changed.
878       Two parameters are passed to the MVEvent.ZOOM_LEVEL_CHANGE listener when it is invoked.
879       The first parameter specifies the map zoom level before the zoom level change 
880       and the second parameter specifies the map zoom level after the zoom level change.</li>
881  *<li>A MVEvent.BEFORE_ZOOM_LEVEL_CHANGE event occurs before the map zoom level is changed.
882       Two parameters are passed to the MVEvent.BEFORE_ZOOM_LEVEL_CHANGE listener when it is invoked.
883       The first parameter specifies the map zoom level before the zoom level change 
884       and the second parameter specifies the map zoom level after the zoom level change.</li>
885  *<li>An MVEvent.INITIALIZE event occurs right after the {@link #display} method is called and the map is initialized and displayed for the first time.
886       No parameter is passed to this listener. </li>
887  *</ul>
888  *@param  {string} eventType one of the following string values identifying the type of event listener:
889   MVEvent.RECENTER, MVEvent.MOUSE_CLICK, MVEvent.MOUSE_RIGHT_CLICK, MVEvent.MOUSE_DOUBLE_CLICK, MVEvent.MOUSE_DOWN, MVEvent.MOUSE_UP, MVEvent.ZOOM_LEVEL_CHANGE, MVEvent.BEFORE_ZOOM_LEVEL_CHANGE and MVEvent.INITIALIZE.
890  *@param {string}listener specifying the listener function.
891  *@returns   None
892  *@type void
893  */ 
894    MVMapView.prototype.attachEventListener = function(type, listener)
895   {
896     MVUtil.attachEventListener(this.EventListeners,type,listener)
897   }
898  /**
899  *This method detaches an event listener that has previously been attached to the map by {@link #attachEventListener}. 
900  *@param  {string} eventType one of the following string values identifying the type of event listener:
901   MVEvent.RECENTER, MVEvent.MOUSE_CLICK, MVEvent.MOUSE_RIGHT_CLICK, MVEvent.MOUSE_DOUBLE_CLICK, MVEvent.ZOOM_LEVEL_CHANGE, MVEvent.BEFORE_ZOOM_LEVEL_CHANGE and MVEvent.INITIALIZE.
902  *@param {string}listener specifying the listener function.
903  *@returns   None
904  *@type void
905  */   
906     MVMapView.prototype.detachEventListener = function(type, listener)
907   {
908     MVUtil.detachEventListener(this.EventListeners,type, listener);
909   }

911  /**
912  @private
913  */
914  MVMapView.prototype.init = function()
915  {
916    this.setFOILayersSize();
917    MVUtil.setLeftTop(this.div, 0, 0);
918    MVUtil.setLeftTop(this.info_div, 0, 0);
919    if (this.infoLayer.infoWindows.length > 0)
920      this.infoLayer.deleteInfoWindow(this.infoLayer.infoWindows[0]); 
921    this.divLeft = 0;
922    this.divTop = 0;
923    this.origLeft = this.divLeft;
924    this.origTop = this.divTop;
925    this.dragOffsetX = 0;
926    this.dragOffsetY = 0; 
927    
928    this.setZoomLevel(this.zoomLevel) ;
929    this.adjustParam() ;
930    // check the center point and make sure the map window does not exceed cs boundary
931    var point = MVSdoGeometry.createPoint(this.mapCenterX, this.mapCenterY, this.srid);
932    point = this.checkMapCenter(point) ;
933    this.mapCenterX = point.getPointX() ;
934    this.mapCenterY = point.getPointY() ;
935    /*this.oldPaneWidth = null ;
936    this.oldPaneHeight = null ;*/
937    this.oldPaneWidth = this.getPaneWidth() ;
938    this.oldPaneHeight = this.getPaneHeight() ;
939    if(this.sizeCheckingHandle)
940      clearTimeout(this.sizeCheckingHandle) ;
941    this.setLoadingIconVisible(true) ;
942    this.mapScreenCenterX = this.mapDrawOffsetX + (this.mapTileNumX / 2 * this.tileWidth);
943    this.mapScreenCenterY = this.mapDrawOffsetY + (this.mapTileNumY / 2 * this.tileHeight);
944    this.do_GetMinCntMesh();
945    if(!this.displayed)
946    {
947     if(this.loadBoundingTheme())
948     {
949       this.loadBoundingTheme = true;
950       return ;
951     }
952    }
953    if (this.scalectl && !this.scalectl.insideMapDecoration && !this.scalectl.initialized)
954      this.addScaleBarControl(this.scalectl);
955    if (this.navigationPanel && !this.navigationPanel.initialized)
956      this.navigationPanel.init(this.base_div, this) ;
957    
958    for(var i=0;i<this.mapLayers.length;i++)
959    {
960      if(this.mapLayers[i].layerControl)
961      {
962        this.mapLayers[i].layerControl.initTiles(this.getPaneWidth(), this.getPaneHeight(), 
963                                                 this.mapCenterX, this.mapCenterY);
964        if(this.mapLayers[i].layerControl && this.mapLayers[i].layerControl.zoomControl.scaling )
965        {
966          this.mapLayers[i].layerControl.zoomControl.endScaling();
967        }
968      }
969      else if(this.mapLayers[i].isExtAPITileLayer())
970      {
971        this.setExternalAPITileLayerCenter(this.mapLayers[i], this.mapCenterX, this.mapCenterY, this.zoomLevel) ;
972      }
973    }
974    //this.setExternalAPITileLayersCenter(this.mapCenterX, this.mapCenterY, this.zoomLevel);
975    if(!this.infoLayer)
976       this.infoLayer = new MVInfoLayerControl(this, "1") ;
977    if(!this.infoLayer2)
978       this.infoLayer2 = new MVInfoLayerControl(this, "2") ;
979    this.do_GetMinMaxLonLat();     
980    this.initMapWindowMinX = this.mapWindowMinLon ;
981    this.initMapWindowMaxY = this.mapWindowMaxLat ;
982    this.transparentLayer.style.zIndex = 125;
983    this.refreshMapContent();
984    this.layer_created = true;
985    this.loaded = true;
986    //add for initial map decoration
987    if (this.mapDecorationArray!=null)
988    for(var i=0;i<this.mapDecorationArray.length;i++)
989      if (this.mapDecorationArray[i]!=null && !this.mapDecorationArray[i].displayed)
990      {
991        var id = "_md_"+this.mapDecorationId
992        this.mapDecorationArray[i].init(id,this,this.base_div);
993        this.mapDecorationId++;
994        this.mapDecorationArray[i].displayed = true ;
995        
996        //add by zhengwan 
997        //call afterDisAction when the mapdecoration success displayed
998        if(this.mapDecorationArray[i].afterDisAction)
999        {
1000         this.mapDecorationArray[i].afterDisAction();
1001        }
1002      }
1003    if (this.overviewmap != null && this.overviewmap.mainmap == null)
1004      this.overviewmap.init(this.overviewmap.overviewMapDIV, this);
1005      
1006    this.checkLayersAndSetLoadingIcon() ;
1007    /*if (this.scalectl)
1008    {
1009      this.scalectl.update(this);
1010    }*/
1011    this.sizeCheckingHandle = this.setTimeout("this.checkSize()", 400) ;
1012    if(!this.displayed || this.loadBoundingTheme)
1013    {
1014      this.displayed = true ;
1015      this.loadBoundingTheme = false;
1016      if(this.initializeListener)
1017         this.initializeListener();
1018      MVUtil.runListeners(this.EventListeners,MVEvent.INITIALIZE);
1019      if(this.isSubmap==undefined || !this.isSubmap)
1020      {
1021        if(MVMapInitializers.length)
1022        {
1023          for(var i=0; i<MVMapInitializers.length; i++)
1024          {
1025            if(MVMapInitializers[i])
1026              MVMapInitializers[i](this) ;
1027          }
1028        }
1029      }
1030    }
1031    window.status = ' ';
1032  }
1033  /**
1034  @private
1035  */
1036  MVMapView.prototype.destroy = function()
1037  {
1038    while(this.mapLayers && this.mapLayers.length>0)
1039    {    
1040      var tileLayer = this.mapLayers.pop();
1041      tileLayer.destroy() ;
1042    }
1043    this.mapLayers = null ;
1044    if(!this.infoLayer)
1045    {
1046      this.infoLayer.destroy() ;
1047      this.infoLayer = null ;
1048    }
1049    while(this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup && this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup.length>0)
1050    {
1051      var layer = this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup.pop();     
1052      layer.destroy() ;
1053    }
1054    while(this.foiGroupArray && this.foiGroupArray.length>0)
1055    {
1056      var group = this.foiGroupArray.pop();
1057      group.destroy() ;
1058    }
1059    this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup = null ;
1060    if(this.indFOIsControl)
1061     this.indFOIsControl.destroy();
1062    this.indFOIsControl = null ;
1063    if(this.mapDecorationArray)
1064     while(this.mapDecorationArray.length>0)
1065     {
1066       var dec = this.mapDecorationArray.pop();
1067       dec.destroy();
1068     }
1069    this.mapDecorationArray = null ;
1070    if (this.overviewmap)
1071    {
1072      this.overviewmap.destroy() ;
1073      this.overviewmap = null ;
1074    }
1075    if(this.toolBar)
1076    {
1077      this.toolBar.destroy() ;
1078      this.toolBar = null ;
1079    }
1080    MVUtil.clearNode(this.base_div, this.errorHandler) ;
1081    this.transImage = null ;
1082    this.base_div = null ;
1083    this.info_div = null; 
1084    this.transparentLayer = null; 
1085    this.div = null; 
1086  }
1087  /**
1088  @private
1089  */
1090  MVMapView.prototype.adjustParam = function()
1091  {
1092    this.tileWidth  = this.TileW[this.zoomLevel];
1093    this.tileHeight = this.TileH[this.zoomLevel];
1094    this.doAdjustParams();
1095  }
1096  /**
1097  @private
1098  */
1099  MVMapView.prototype.doAdjustParams = function()
1100  {
1101    this.mapDrawOffsetX =  - this.tileWidth * this.mapCacheOffSet;
1102    this.mapDrawOffsetY =  - this.tileHeight * this.mapCacheOffSet;
1103    var t1 = this.getPaneWidth()/this.tileWidth ;
1104    this.mapTileNumX = parseInt(Math.ceil(t1/2)+ 1) * 2+1;
1105    t1=this.getPaneHeight()/this.tileHeight;
1106    this.mapTileNumY = parseInt(Math.ceil(t1/2) + 1) * 2+1;
1107    this.mapScreenCenterX = this.mapDrawOffsetX + (this.mapTileNumX / 2 * this.tileWidth); // map center X
1108    this.mapScreenCenterY = this.mapDrawOffsetY + (this.mapTileNumY / 2 * this.tileHeight); // map center Y
1109    var levelDef = this.msi.mapConfig.zoomLevels[this.zoomLevel] ;
1110    this.pixPerX = levelDef.tileImageWidth / levelDef.tileWidth; // pixel per 1 degree
1111    this.pixPerY = levelDef.tileImageHeight / levelDef.tileHeight; // pixel per 1 degree
1112  }
1113  /**
1114  @private
1115  */ 
1116  MVMapView.prototype.do_GetMinCntMesh = function()
1117  { 
1118    this.mapCntMesh = new MVMesh(this.msi.mapConfig,this.mapCenterX, this.mapCenterY,this.zoomLevel); // CenterMesh
1119    this.mapMinMesh = new MVMesh(this.msi.mapConfig,this.mapCenterX, this.mapCenterY,this.zoomLevel); // MinMesh
1120    this.mapMinMesh.moveMeshCode( - (Math.ceil(this.mapTileNumX / 2) - 1),  + Math.ceil(this.mapTileNumY / 2) - 1);
1121  }
1122  /**
1123  @private
1124  */ 
1125  MVMapView.prototype.do_GetMinMaxLonLat= function ()
1126  {
1127    this.mapMinLon = this.mapMinMesh.minX;
1128    this.mapMinLat = (this.mapMinMesh.minY + this.mapMinMesh.mh);
1129    this.mapMaxLon = (this.mapMinMesh.minX + (this.mapMinMesh.mw * this.mapTileNumX));
1130    this.mapMaxLat = (this.mapMinMesh.minY - (this.mapMinMesh.mh * (this.mapTileNumY - 1)));
1131  
1132    // get precise min max lon lat value
1133    this.mapWindowMinLon = this.getMapWindowMinX(this.mapCenterX);
1134    this.mapWindowMinLat = this.getMapWindowMinY(this.mapCenterY);
1135    this.mapWindowMaxLon = this.getMapWindowMaxX(this.mapCenterX);
1136    this.mapWindowMaxLat = this.getMapWindowMaxY(this.mapCenterY);
1137  }
1138  /**
1139  *This method initializes the map and displays the map content inside the 
1140  *map container (which is an HTML DIV element defined in the web page). This 
1141  *method should only be called when the map is displayed for the first time or needs
1142  *to be reloaded. 
1143  *@returns   None
1144  *@type void
1145  */
1146  MVMapView.prototype.display = function()
1147  {
1148    var mv = this ;
1149    var checkSizeAndDisplay = function()
1150    {
1151     var w = 0 ;
1152     if(!mv.base_div)
1153       return ;
1154     if(mv.base_div.offsetWidth)
1155       w = parseInt(mv.base_div.offsetWidth+"");
1156     else if(typeof(mv.base_div.offsetWidth)=="undefined")
1157       w = mv.getPaneWidth() ;
1158     var h = 0 ;
1159     if(mv.base_div.offsetHeight)
1160       h = parseInt(mv.base_div.offsetHeight+"");
1161     else if(typeof(mv.base_div.offsetHeight)=="undefined")
1162       h = mv.getPaneHeight() ;
1163     if(!MVi18n.isFetched() || w<=0 || h<=0 || !mv.tileLayersConfigLoaded() ||
1164        !MVGlobalVariables.transImageLoaded || !mv.msi)
1165     {
1166       setTimeout(checkSizeAndDisplay, 200) ;
1167       return ;
1168     }
1169     var callBack = function()
1170     {
1171       mv.init();
1172       if(!mv.handlersAdded)
1173       {
1174         mv.addEventHandlers();
1175         mv.handlersAdded = true ;
1176       } 
1177       mv.displayed=true;
1178       while(mv.delayedOperations.length>0)
1179       {
1180         var oper = mv.delayedOperations.shift() ;
1181         if(oper.func=="refreshFOIs")
1182           oper.obj.refreshFOIs(oper.params[0], oper.params[1], oper.params[2], oper.params[3], oper.params[4], oper.params[5], oper.params[6], oper.params[7], true, oper.params[8]) ;
1183         else if(oper.func=="zoomToRectangle")
1184           oper.obj.zoomToRectangle(oper.params[0], oper.params[1]) ;
1185         else if(oper.func=="refresh")
1186           oper.obj.refresh(oper.params[0]) ;
1187       }
1188     }
1189     mv.setCenterXY(callBack) ;
1190    }
1191    checkSizeAndDisplay();
1192  }
1193 
1194  //========================== Set method for MVMapView=========================
1195  /**
1196  *This method sets the center of the current map. The map center is defined in 
1197  *the map coordinate system and is specified as an MVSdoGeometry point object.
1198  *@param {MVSdoGeometry} mpoint an MVSdoGeometry point object that specifies the map center
1199  *@param {Boolean} noSmoothPanning whether not to pan the map in a animated sliding manner. True if no smooth panning, false otherwise.
1200  *@returns   None
1201  *@type void
1202  */
1203  MVMapView.prototype.setCenter = function( mpoint, noSmoothPanning)
1204  {
1205    this.reCenterTag = true;
1206    this.center = mpoint ;
1207    this.originalCenter = mpoint
1208    if(this.displayed)
1209      this.setCenterXY(null, noSmoothPanning);
1210  }
1211  /**@private*/
1212  MVMapView.prototype.setCenterXY = function(topLevelCallBack, noSmoothPanning)
1213  {
1214    if(!this.center)
1215    {
1216      if(topLevelCallBack)
1217       topLevelCallBack();
1218      return ;
1219    }
1220    if(!this.msi)
1221    {
1222      MVi18n.reportError("MVMapView.setCenter", "MAPVIEWER-05518", null, this.errorHandler) ;
1223      return ;
1224    }
1225    this.srid =  this.msi.getSrid();
1226    var mpoint = this.center ;
1227    if(!this.reCenterTag && this.originalCenter!=null)
1228      mpoint = this.originalCenter;
1229    if (mpoint)
1230    {
1231      if(!mpoint.srid)
1232        mpoint.srid = this.srid ;
1233      this.center = null ;
1234      if(!(mpoint.sdo_point))
1235      {
1236        MVi18n.reportError("MVMapView.setCenter", "MAPVIEWER-05505", null, this.errorHandler);
1237        return ;
1238      }
1239      var mv = this;
1240      var callBack=function(newPoint)
1241      {
1242       if(newPoint)
1243         mpoint = newPoint ;
1244       if(mv.displayed)
1245         mpoint = mv.checkMapCenter(mpoint) ;
1246 
1247       var hasExternalAPITileLayer = false
1248       for(var i=0; i<mv.mapLayers.length; i++)
1249       {
1250         if(mv.mapLayers[i].isExtAPITileLayer())
1251           hasExternalAPITileLayer = true;
1252       }
1253       if (!mv.displayed) // || hasExternalAPITileLayer )
1254       {
1255         mv.mapCenterX =  mpoint.getPointX();
1256         mv.mapCenterY =  mpoint.getPointY();
1257         mv.setExternalAPITileLayersCenter(mpoint.getPointX(), mpoint.getPointY());
1258       }
1259       else
1260       {
1261         if (mv.mapCenterX != mv.originalCenter.getPointX() || mv.mapCenterY != mv.originalCenter.getPointY()) 
1262         {
1263           mv.map_moveX = (mv.mapCenterX - mpoint.getPointX())*mv.pixPerX ;
1264           mv.map_moveY = (mv.mapCenterY - mpoint.getPointY())*mv.pixPerY*(-1);
1265         }
1266         else
1267         {
1268           mv.map_moveX = 0;
1269           mv.map_moveY = 0;
1270         }
1271         mv.panWidth = mv.getPaneWidth();
1272         mv.panHeight = mv.getPaneHeight();
1273         if (Math.abs(mv.map_moveX)<=(mv.panWidth+mv.mapBufferX) && Math.abs(mv.map_moveY)<=(mv.panHeight+mv.mapBufferY))
1274         {
1275           mv.distance = Math.sqrt(mv.map_moveX * mv.map_moveX + mv.map_moveY * mv.map_moveY);
1276           mv.stepTime = 20;
1277           mv.totalTime = mv.distance > ((mv.panWidth + mv.panHeight)/4)?300:200;
1278           mv.loopCount = 0;
1279           mv.curX = 0;
1280           mv.curY = 0;
1281           mv.smoothPan(noSmoothPanning);
1282         }
1283         else
1284         {
1285           mv.mapCenterX =  mpoint.getPointX();
1286           mv.mapCenterY =  mpoint.getPointY();
1287           mv.display();
1288           //fix bug 6963467
1289           if (mv.recenterListener)
1290           { 
1291             mv.recenterListener();
1292           }
1293           MVUtil.runListeners(mv.EventListeners,MVEvent.RECENTER);
1294         }
1295         if(mv.scalectl)
1296         {
1297           mv.scalectl.update(mv) ;
1298         }
1299       }
1300       if(topLevelCallBack)
1301         topLevelCallBack();
1302      }
1303      if (this.srid != mpoint.srid)
1304      {
1305        this.reCenterTag = true;
1306        mpoint = this.transformGeom(mpoint, this.srid, null, callBack);
1307      }
1308      else
1309        callBack();
1310    }
1311    else
1312    {
1313     if(topLevelCallBack)
1314       topLevelCallBack();
1315    }
1316  }

1331  /**
1332  *This method displays an image marker at the center of the current map.
1333  *The center marker does not move when the map is being dragged.
1334  *@param {string} img_url a string that specifies the URL of the center mark image.
1335  *@param  {int} img_width  specifies the width of the image marker.
1336  *@param  {int} img_height specifies the height of the image marker.
1337  *@returns   None
1338  *@type void
1339  */
1340  MVMapView.prototype.setCenterMark = function(img_url, img_width, img_height)
1341  {
1342    if (this.center_mark != undefined)
1343    {
1344      this.base_div.removeChild(this.center_mark);
1345      delete this.center_mark;
1346    }
1347    if (img_url == null)
1348      return ;
1349  
1350    this.centerMarkUrl = img_url;
1351    this.centerMarkW = img_width;
1352    this.centerMarkH = img_height;
1353 
1354    var mark = document.createElement("img"); //new Image();
1355    mark.src = img_url;
1356    mark.style.zIndex = 2000;
1357    mark.style.position = "absolute";
1358    mark.style.width = MVUtil.pixel(img_width);
1359    mark.style.height = MVUtil.pixel(img_height);
1360    mark.style.left = MVUtil.pixel((this.getPaneWidth() - img_width)/2);
1361    mark.style.top = MVUtil.pixel((this.getPaneHeight() - img_height)/2);
1362    this.base_div.appendChild(mark);
1363    this.center_mark = mark;
1364  } 
1365  /**
1366  *This method sets the current zoom level of the map.
1367  *@param {int} zoom an integer that specifies the map zoom level.
1368  *@returns   None
1369  *@type void
1370  */
1371  MVMapView.prototype.setZoomLevel = function(zoom)
1372  {
1373    if(isNaN(zoom))
1374    {
1375      MVi18n.reportError("MVMapView.setZoomLevel", "MAPVIEWER-05506", null, this.errorHandler);
1376      return;
1377    }
1378    if( (!this.displayed) && this.msi == null )
1379    {
1380      this.zoomLevel = zoom ;
1381      return ;
1382    }
1383    if(zoom<0)
1384      zoom = 0 ;
1385    else if(zoom>this.maxZoom)
1386      zoom = this.maxZoom ;
1387    /*MVi18n.reportError(zoom) ;
1388    if(zoom<0 || this.maxZoom && zoom>this.maxZoom)
1389      MVi18n.reportError("The zoom level specified is invalid: out of range, and it should be an integer between 0 and "+this.maxZoom+". Error: setZoomLevel(...) in MapView");*/
1390    if (this.displayed)
1391      this.zoomTo(zoom);
1392    else
1393    {
1394      this.zoomLevel = zoom;
1395      //this.getZoom().setZoomValue(zoom);
1396      this.adjustParam();
1397    }
1398  }
1399  /**
1400   This method sets the home map location and zoom level. When the 
1401   home map location and zoom level is set, the user can click on the center 
1402   button of the navigation panel to bring the map back to its home location 
1403   and zoom level. 
1404  
1405   @param {MVSdoGeometry} center an MVSdoGeometry point object that specifies the home/original center.
1406   @param {int} zoomlevel an integer that specifies the home/original zoom level
1407  */
1408  MVMapView.prototype.setHomeMap = function(center, zoomlevel)
1409  {
1410    this.originLocation=center;
1411    if(zoomlevel)
1412      this.originZoomLevel=zoomlevel;
1413  }

1422  /**
1423  @private
1424  */
1425  MVMapView.prototype.setProvider = function(mapTileLayer, afterSetProvider)
1426  {
1427    var redrawEverything = false ;
1428    var mv = this ;
1429    
1430    var callBackSetProvider = function(mpoint)
1431    {
1432     if(mpoint)
1433     {
1434       mv.mapCenterX =  mpoint.getPointX();
1435       mv.mapCenterY =  mpoint.getPointY();
1436       mv.center = mpoint ;
1437     }
1438          
1439     mv.msi = mapTileLayer.msi ;
1440     mv.srid = mv.msi.getSrid() ;
1441     mv.maptype = mv.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.type;
1442     //this.msi.init();
1443     //if (this.zoomLevel > (this.getZoom().getZoomCount() - 1))
1444     if (mv.zoomLevel > (mv.msi.zoomCount - 1))
1445     {
1446       //this.zoomLevel = this.getZoom().getZoomCount() - 1;
1447       mv.zoomLevel = mv.msi.zoomCount - 1;
1448     }
1449     //this.getZoom().setZoomValue(this.zoomLevel);
1450   
1451     for (var i = 0; i < mv.msi.getMaxZoomLevel(); i++)
1452     {
1453       mv.TileW[i] = mv.msi.getTileImageWidth(mv.zoomLevel);
1454       mv.TileH[i] = mv.msi.getTileImageHeight(mv.zoomLevel);
1455     }
1456     mv.adjustParam();
1457     mv.maxZoom = mv.msi.getMaxZoomLevel()-1;
1458     mv.do_GetMinCntMesh(); 
1459         
1460     afterSetProvider(redrawEverything) ;
1461   
1462    }
1463    
1464    if(!mapTileLayer.msi)
1465      mapTileLayer.msi = new MVMapProvider(mapTileLayer.mapSource);
1466    if(this.msi)
1467    {
1468      //Compare with the tile layer of mv.
1469      if(mapTileLayer.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.srid != this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.srid || mapTileLayer.msi.mapConfig.zoomLevels.length != this.msi.mapConfig.zoomLevels.length)
1470      {
1471        redrawEverything = true ;
1472      }
1473      else
1474      {
1475        for(var x=0;x<this.msi.mapConfig.zoomLevels.length;x++)
1476        {
1477          var oneZoomLevelOfCurrentTileLayer = mapTileLayer.msi.mapConfig.zoomLevels[x];
1478          var oneZoomLevelOfMvTileLayer = this.msi.mapConfig.zoomLevels[x];
1479          var xScaleOfCurrent = oneZoomLevelOfCurrentTileLayer.tileWidth / oneZoomLevelOfCurrentTileLayer.tileImageWidth;
1480          var yScaleOfCurrent =  oneZoomLevelOfCurrentTileLayer.tileHeight /   oneZoomLevelOfCurrentTileLayer.tileImageHeight;
1481          var xScaleOfMv = oneZoomLevelOfMvTileLayer.tileWidth / oneZoomLevelOfMvTileLayer.tileImageWidth;
1482          var yScaleOfMv = oneZoomLevelOfMvTileLayer.tileHeight / oneZoomLevelOfMvTileLayer.tileImageHeight;
1483          if(xScaleOfCurrent != xScaleOfMv|| yScaleOfCurrent != yScaleOfMv)
1484          {
1485            redrawEverything = true ;
1486            break;
1487          }
1488        }
1489      }
1490 
1491      if(!mapTileLayer.isVisible() || this.msi.getSrid() == mapTileLayer.msi.getSrid())
1492      {
1493        //afterSetProvider(false) ;
1494        callBackSetProvider() ;
1495        return;
1496      }
1497      else
1498      {
1499        redrawEverything = true ;
1500        var mpoint = MVSdoGeometry.createPoint(this.mapCenterX, this.mapCenterY, this.msi.getSrid()) ;
1501        
1502        if(!this.reCenterTag && this.originalCenter!=null)
1503           mpoint = this.originalCenter;
1504        
1505        this.transformGeom(mpoint, mapTileLayer.msi.getSrid(), null, callBackSetProvider);
1506 
1507      }
1508    }
1509    else
1510      callBackSetProvider() ;
1511      
1512  }

1522  /**
1523  @private
1524  */
1525  MVMapView.prototype.getPaneWidth = function()
1526  {
1527    var w = 0 ;
1528    if(this.base_div.style && this.base_div.style.width)
1529    {
1530      var wStr = this.base_div.style.width+"" ;
1531      if(wStr.indexOf("%")<0)
1532      {
1533        if(wStr.indexOf("px")>0)
1534          w = parseInt(wStr.substring(0, wStr.indexOf("px"))) ;
1535        else
1536          w = parseInt(wStr) ;
1537        if(w)
1538          return w ;
1539      }
1540    }
1541    if(this.base_div.offsetWidth)
1542      w = this.base_div.offsetWidth;
1543    else if(this.base_div.width)
1544      w = parseInt(this.base_div.width+"") ;
1545    return w ;
1546  }
1547  /**
1548  @private
1549  */ 
1550  MVMapView.prototype.getPaneHeight = function()
1551  {
1552    var h = 0 ;
1553    if(this.base_div.style && this.base_div.style.height)
1554    {
1555      var wStr = this.base_div.style.height+"" ;
1556      if(wStr.indexOf("%")<0)
1557      {
1558        if(wStr.indexOf("px")>0)
1559          h = parseInt(wStr.substring(0, wStr.indexOf("px"))) ;
1560        else
1561          h = parseInt(wStr) ;
1562        if(h)
1563          return h ;
1564      }
1565    }
1566    if(this.base_div.offsetHeight)
1567      h = this.base_div.offsetHeight;
1568    else if(this.base_div.width)
1569      h = parseInt(this.base_div.width+"");
1570    return h ;
1571  }
1572  /**
1573  @private
1574  */
1575  MVMapView.prototype.getMapWindowMinX = function(mapCenterX)
1576  {
1577    var t1 = this.getPaneWidth()/2 ;
1578    return (0-t1)/this.pixPerX + mapCenterX;
1579  }
1580  /**
1581  @private
1582  */
1583  MVMapView.prototype.getMapWindowMinY = function(mapCenterY)
1584  {
1585   var t1 = this.getPaneHeight()/2;
1586   return -1.0*(t1 - 1 )/this.pixPerY + mapCenterY;
1587  }
1588  /**
1589  @private
1590  */ 
1591  MVMapView.prototype.getMapWindowMaxX = function(mapCenterX)
1592  {
1593    var t1=this.getPaneWidth()/2;
1594    return (t1-1 )/this.pixPerX + mapCenterX;
1595  }
1596  /**
1597  @private
1598  */
1599  MVMapView.prototype.getMapWindowMaxY = function(mapCenterY)
1600  {
1601   var t1=this.getPaneHeight()/2;
1602   return -1.0*( 0 - t1)/this.pixPerY + mapCenterY;
1603  }

1673  /**
1674  *This method gets the maximum zoom level of the map.
1675  *@returns {int} The maximum zoom level.
1676  */
1677  MVMapView.prototype.getMaxZoomLevel = function()
1678  {
1679    if(!this.msi)
1680    {
1681      MVi18n.reportError("MVMapView.getMaxZoomLevel", "MAPVIEWER-05526", null, this.errorHandler) ;
1682      return -1 ;
1683    }
1684    else
1685      return this.msi.getMaxZoomLevel();
1686  }

1689   * the map can only be dragged within the map area defined by the map coordinate system 
1690   * bounding box, and the map will be automatically centered to the map coordinate system 
1691   * center when the map is at a zoom level where the map DIV container is wider than the 
1692   * whole map area. By default, map bound constraint is enabled.
1693   */
1694  MVMapView.prototype.enableMapBoundConstraint = function(enable)
1695  {
1696    return this.enforceCSBound = enable;
1697  }

1813  //===================Zoom Method for MVMapView=======================
1814  /**
1815  *This method zooms the map in by one zoom level.
1816  *@param {MVSdoGeometry}center optional, an MVSdoGeometry that specifies the 
1817  *                      new center of the map after zooming.
1818  *@returns   None
1819  *@type void
1820  */
1821  MVMapView.prototype.zoomIn = function(center)
1822  {
1823    this.zoomTo(this.zoomLevel + 1,center);
1824  }
1825  /**
1826  *This method zooms the map out by one zoom level.
1827  *@param {MVSdoGeometry} center optional, an MVSdoGeometry that specifies the 
1828                         new center of the map after zooming.
1829  *@returns   None
1830  *@type void
1831  */
1832  MVMapView.prototype.zoomOut = function(center)
1833  {
1834    this.zoomTo(this.zoomLevel - 1,center);
1835  }
1836  /**
1837    This method enables or disables zoom animation. 
1838    If enabledOrNot is true, animation effect will show when zoom in/out. 
1839 
1840    @param {boolean} enabledOrNot a boolean value which indicates whether or not to enable zoom animation
1841    @returns  None
1842    @type     void
1843  */ 
1844  MVMapView.prototype.setZoomAnimationEnabled = function(enabledOrNot)
1845  {
1846    this.zoomAnimationEnabled = enabledOrNot;
1847  }
1848  /**
1849  @private
1850  */
1851  MVMapView.prototype.zoomTo = function(level,center, noAnimation, forceRefresh)
1852  {
1853    var mv = this ;
1854    if(mv.beforeZoomLevel<0)
1855      mv.beforeZoomLevel = mv.zoomLevel;
1856    
1857    var realZoom = function()
1858    {
1859     mv.zoomToCounter = 0 ;
1860     mv.zoomToTimer = null;
1861     if (level >= mv.maxZoom)
1862     {
1863       level = mv.maxZoom;  
1864     }
1865     else if (level < 0)
1866     {
1867       level = 0; 
1868     }  
1869     
1870     if (!forceRefresh && mv.afterZoomLevel==mv.zoomLevel && level == mv.zoomLevel && !center)
1871     {
1872       if (mv.navigationPanel)
1873         mv.navigationPanel.updateSliderBar() ;
1874       return false;
1875     }
1876     mv.printReset();
1877   
1878     mv.zoomLevel = level; 
1879     
1880     if (mv.navigationPanel)
1881       mv.navigationPanel.updateSliderBar() ;
1882     //this.setZoomLevel(this.zoomLevel);
1883     
1884     mv.zoomLevel = level;
1885     //this.getZoom().setZoomValue(level);
1886     mv.adjustParam();
1887     var recenterEnable = false;
1888   
1889     var oldCenter=MVSdoGeometry.createPoint(mv.mapCenterX, mv.mapCenterY, mv.srid);
1890     var callBack = function(newCenter)
1891     {
1892       if(newCenter)
1893         center = newCenter ;
1894       if(mv.m_scroll_id)
1895       {
1896         clearTimeout(mv.m_scroll_id) ;
1897         mv.m_scroll_id = null;
1898       }
1899       if (center)
1900       {
1901         if (center.getPointX()!=mv.mapCenterX || center.getPointY()!=mv.mapCenterY)
1902         {
1903           recenterEnable = true;
1904         }
1905         mv.mapCenterX =  center.getPointX();
1906         mv.mapCenterY =  center.getPointY();  
1907       }
1908       if (mv.beforeZoomListener && mv.beforeZoomLevel!=mv.zoomLevel)
1909         mv.beforeZoomListener(mv.beforeZoomLevel, mv.zoomLevel) ;
1910       if(mv.beforeZoomLevel!=mv.zoomLevel)
1911           MVUtil.runListeners(mv.EventListeners,MVEvent.BEFORE_ZOOM_LEVEL_CHANGE,[mv.beforeZoomLevel, mv.zoomLevel]);
1912           
1913       //Add by Raymond   zoom animation
1914       var display = function()
1915       {
1916         if (Math.abs(mv.beforeZoomLevel-mv.zoomLevel)==1 && mv.displayCounter<=1 && mv.zoomAnimationEnabled && !noAnimation) 
1917         {
1918           for(var i=0; i< mv.mapLayers.length; i++)
1919           {
1920             if(mv.mapLayers[i].layerControl && !mv.mapLayers[i].layerControl.zoomControl.scaling)
1921               mv.mapLayers[i].layerControl.zoomControl.showTiles(mv.beforeZoomLevel, mv.zoomLevel, oldCenter, center);
1922           }
1923         }
1924         
1925         mv.display();
1926         mv.displayCounter = 0 ;
1927         mv.displayTimer = null ;
1928         mv.afterZoomLevel = mv.zoomLevel ;
1929         if (recenterEnable)
1930         {
1931         if(mv.recenterListener)
1932             mv.recenterListener();
1933         MVUtil.runListeners(mv.EventListeners,MVEvent.RECENTER);
1934         }
1935       
1936         if (mv.overviewmap)
1937         {
1938           mv.overviewmap.zoomMainMap(mv.beforeZoomLevel,mv.zoomLevel);
1939           var refreshSubMap = function(){
1940             mv.overviewmap.refreshSubMap();
1941           }
1942           setTimeout(refreshSubMap,200);
1943         }
1944         if (mv.beforeZoomLevel!=mv.zoomLevel)
1945         {
1946           var before_zoomLevel = mv.beforeZoomLevel ;
1947           mv.beforeZoomLevel = -1 ;
1948           if(mv.zoomListener) 
1949               mv.zoomListener(before_zoomLevel,mv.zoomLevel);
1950           MVUtil.runListeners(mv.EventListeners,MVEvent.ZOOM_LEVEL_CHANGE,[before_zoomLevel, mv.zoomLevel]);
1951         }
1952       }
1953       
1954       if(!mv.displayCounter)
1955         mv.displayCounter = 0 ;
1956       mv.displayCounter++ ;
1957       if(mv.displayTimer)
1958         clearTimeout(mv.displayTimer) ;
1959       mv.displayTimer = setTimeout(display, 200) ;
1960       
1961       if(mv.scalectl)
1962       {
1963         mv.scalectl.update(mv);
1964       }
1965     }
1966     if (center)
1967     {
1968       mv.reCenterTag = true;
1969       mv.srid =  mv.msi.getSrid();
1970       if(!center.srid)
1971         center.srid = mv.srid ;
1972       if(!(center.sdo_point))
1973       {
1974         MVi18n.reportError("MVMapView.zoomTo", "MAPVIEWER-05505", null, mv.errorHandler);
1975         return ;
1976       }
1977         
1978       if (center.srid && (mv.srid != center.srid))
1979         center = mv.transformGeom(center, mv.srid,null, callBack);
1980       else
1981         callBack(); 
1982     }
1983     else
1984       callBack();
1985     return true;
1986    }
1987    if(!this.zoomToCounter)
1988      this.zoomToCounter = 0 ;
1989    this.zoomToCounter++ ;
1990    if(mv.displayTimer)
1991    {
1992      clearTimeout(mv.displayTimer) ;
1993      mv.displayTimer = null ;
1994    }
1995    if(this.zoomToTimer)
1996      clearTimeout(this.zoomToTimer) ;
1997    if(this.zoomToCounter<2)
1998      this.zoomToTimer = setTimeout(realZoom, 200) ;
1999    else
2000    {
2001      realZoom() ;
2002      return ;
2003    }
2004  }
2005  /**
2006    @private
2007    The method will zoom in/out the map at given location
2008    @param {Object} point point is a MVSdoGeometry object.It specifies the given location;
2009    @param {int} zoomlevel It should be valid zoom level.
2010    @returns None
2011    @type void
2012  */
2013  MVMapView.prototype.zoomToAtLocation=function(point,zoomlevel)
2014  {
2015    this.srid =  this.msi.getSrid();
2016    var mv = this ;
2017    var callBack = function(newPoint)
2018    {
2019     if(newPoint)
2020       point = newPoint;
2021     var pixX=(mv.mapCenterX-point.getPointX())*mv.pixPerX;
2022     var pixY=(mv.mapCenterY-point.getPointY())*mv.pixPerY;
2023     var newPixPerX=mv.TileW[zoomlevel]/mv.msi.getTileWidth(zoomlevel);
2024     var newPixPerY=mv.TileH[zoomlevel]/mv.msi.getTileHeight(zoomlevel);
2025     var newCenterX=pixX/newPixPerX+point.getPointX();
2026     var newCenterY=pixY/newPixPerY+point.getPointY();
2027     
2028     var newCenter=MVSdoGeometry.createPoint(newCenterX,newCenterY,mv.srid);
2029     mv.zoomTo(zoomlevel,newCenter);
2030    }
2031    if (point.srid && (this.srid != point.srid))
2032      point = this.transformGeom(point, this.srid, null, callBack);
2033    else 
2034      callBack() ;
2035  }
2036  
2037  /**
2038    This method sets the map center and zoom level. 
2039    @param {MVSdoGeometry} center an MVSdoGeometry point object that specifies the map center.
2040    @param {int} zoomLevel an integer that specifies a valid zoom level.
2041  */
2042  MVMapView.prototype.setCenterAndZoomLevel=function(center,zoomLevel)
2043  {
2044    if(!this.displayed)
2045    {
2046      this.center = center ;
2047      this.zoomLevel = zoomLevel ;
2048      this.originalCenter = center;
2049      return ;
2050    }
2051    this.srid =  this.msi.getSrid();
2052    if(!center.srid)
2053      center.srid = this.srid ;
2054    var mv = this ;
2055    var callBack = function(newCenter)
2056    {
2057     if(newCenter)
2058       center = newCenter;
2059     if (zoomLevel==null)
2060     {
2061       zoomLevel=mv.zoomLevel;
2062     }
2063     if (!mv.displayed)
2064     {
2065       mv.setCenter(center) ;
2066       mv.setZoomLevel(zoomLevel) ;
2067       return ;
2068     }
2069     if (zoomLevel==mv.zoomLevel)
2070     {
2071       if(!mv.loaded) 
2072       {
2073         //no tiles have ever been displayed; could happen due to presence of bounding theme 
2074         //e.g. bug 5931525
2075         mv.zoomTo(zoomLevel, center);
2076         return;
2077       }
2078       else //does a smooth pan
2079       {
2080         mv.map_moveX = (mv.mapCenterX - center.getPointX())*mv.pixPerX
2081         mv.map_moveY = (mv.mapCenterY - center.getPointY())*mv.pixPerY*(-1);
2082         mv.panWidth = mv.getPaneWidth();
2083         mv.panHeight = mv.getPaneHeight();
2084         if (Math.abs(mv.map_moveX)<=(mv.panWidth+mv.mapBufferX) && Math.abs(mv.map_moveY)<=(mv.panHeight+mv.mapBufferY))
2085         {
2086           mv.distance = Math.sqrt(mv.map_moveX * mv.map_moveX + mv.map_moveY * mv.map_moveY);
2087           mv.stepTime = 20;
2088           mv.totalTime = mv.distance > ((mv.panWidth + mv.panHeight)/4)?300:200;
2089           mv.loopCount = 0;
2090           mv.curX = 0;
2091           mv.curY = 0;
2092           mv.smoothPan();
2093           return;
2094         }
2095       }
2096     }
2097     mv.zoomTo(zoomLevel,center);
2098    }
2099    if (center.srid && (this.srid != center.srid))
2100      center = this.transformGeom(center, this.srid, null, callBack);
2101    else
2102      callBack() ;
2103  }
2104  
2105  /**
2106    This method adds and displays a map tile layer to the map. 
2107    <p>If the map tile layer is defined on the server(not a MVCustomMapTileLayer object), the map 
2108    client will automatically fetch the map tile layer definition by sending
2109    a request to the map tile server.
2110    
2111    @param {object} mapTileLayer a MVMapTileLayer, MVCustomMapTileLayer, MVGoogleTileLayer,
2112                    MVVirtualEarthTileLayer or MVYahooTileLayer object.
2113    @param {function} callBack the call back function that is execuated after the
2114                      map tile layer configuration is fetched from the server and the 
2115                      map tile layer is added. 
2116    @returns   None
2117    @type void
2118  */
2119  MVMapView.prototype.addMapTileLayer = function (mapTileLayer, callBack) 
2120  {
2121     if(mapTileLayer.getType && mapTileLayer.getType()=="MVExternalAPIMapTileLayer")
2122       this.addExternalAPITileLayer(mapTileLayer);
2123     else
2124     {
2125       if(mapTileLayer.mapSource==undefined ||
2126         mapTileLayer.mapSource==null || 
2127         MVUtil.strTrim(mapTileLayer.mapSource)=="")
2128       {
2129         MVi18n.reportError("MVMapView.addMapTileLayer", "MAPVIEWER-05507", null, this.errorHandler);
2130         return ;
2131       }
2132       // set default data source
2133       if(!this.defaultDataSource && this.compareBaseURL(mapTileLayer.mcsURL))
2134       {
2135         var sourceArray=mapTileLayer.mapSource.split(".");
2136         if (sourceArray.length>=2)
2137         {
2138           MVGlobalVariables.setDefaultDataSource(sourceArray[0]);
2139           this.setDefaultDataSource(sourceArray[0]) ;
2140         }  
2141       }
2142       mapTileLayer.parent = this;
2143       if (!mapTileLayer.mcsURL)
2144       {
2145         if (this.baseURL)
2146         {
2147           if (MVUtil.strEndWith(this.baseURL, '/'))
2148             mapTileLayer.mcsURL = this.baseURL + 'mcserver';
2149           else
2150             mapTileLayer.mcsURL = this.baseURL + '/mcserver';
2151         }
2152         else
2153         {
2154           MVi18n.reportError("MVMapView.addMapTileLayer", "MAPVIEWER-05504",null, this.errorHandler);
2155           return ;
2156         }
2157       }
2158       mapTileLayer.mcscfgURL = mapTileLayer.mcsURL;
2159         
2160       if(mapTileLayer == null || !mapTileLayer.getType)
2161       {
2162         MVi18n.reportError("MVMapView.addMapTileLayer", "MAPVIEWER-05519", "mapTileLayer", this.errorHandler);
2163         return; 
2164       }
2165       
2166       this.mapLayers.push(mapTileLayer);
2167       
2168       /*for (var i = 0; i < this.mapLayers.length; i++)
2169       {
2170         if (this.mapLayers[i].mcsURL == mapTileLayer.mcsURL && 
2171             this.mapLayers[i].mapSource == mapTileLayer.mapSource)
2172         { 
2173           if(callBack)
2174             callBack() ;
2175           return ;
2176         }   
2177       }*/
2178     }      
2179     var mv = this ;
2180     var postProcess = function()
2181     {
2182       mv.mapLayerNumber ++ ;
2183       if(!mapTileLayer.zIndex)
2184         mapTileLayer.zIndex = mv.mapLayers.length + 1 ;
2185       mv.setProvider(mapTileLayer, AfterSetProvider);
2186       mv.showEmbeddedCopyright() ;
2187 
2188       function AfterSetProvider(redraw)
2189       {
2190         mapTileLayer.config = MVGlobal_CacheConfig[mapTileLayer.mapSource] ;
2191         if(!mapTileLayer.isExtAPITileLayer())
2192         {
2193           var  layerControl=mv.getTileLayerControl(mapTileLayer);
2194           mapTileLayer.layerControl = layerControl ;
2195           mv.combineTileLayers() ;
2196         }
2197         //Above all, if only the process goes here, the length of mapLayers should be at least 1.
2198         //If the length of map layers is 1, then the array can be inferred to be empty before calling the method of addMapTileLayer.
2199         //That's to say no single one map tile layer is in the current map. Then error message should not be displayed and removeMapTileLayer
2200         // should also not be called.
2201         if(redraw && mv.mapLayers.length>1)
2202         {
2203           if(!mv.overview)
2204             MVi18n.reportError("MVMapView.addMapTileLayer", "MAPVIEWER-05528", null, this.errorHandler);
2205           for(var i=0; i<mv.mapLayers.length; i++)
2206           {
2207             if(mv.mapLayers[i]!= mapTileLayer)
2208               mv.removeMapTileLayer(mv.mapLayers[i]);
2209           }
2210         }
2211 
2212         if (mv.displayed)
2213         {
2214           if(!redraw)
2215           {
2216             if(mapTileLayer.isExtAPITileLayer())
2217             {
2218               var setExtMapCenter = function(point)
2219               {
2220                 mapTileLayer.setCenterAndZoomLevel(point.getPointX(), point.getPointY(), mv.zoomLevel) ;
2221                 //mapTileLayer.display();
2222               }
2223               var mpoint = MVSdoGeometry.createPoint(mv.mapCenterX, mv.mapCenterY, mv.srid) ;
2224               mv.transformGeom(mpoint, mapTileLayer.srid, null, setExtMapCenter);
2225             }
2226             else
2227             {
2228               if(mapTileLayer.layerControl)
2229                 mapTileLayer.layerControl.initTiles(mv.getPaneWidth(), mv.getPaneHeight(), mv.mapCenterX, mv.mapCenterY);
2230             }
2231           }
2232           else 
2233           {
2234             mv.display() ;
2235           }
2236           if(mv.scalectl)
2237           {
2238             mv.scalectl.update(mv);
2239           }
2240           if (mv.navigationPanel && mv.navigationPanel.getMaxZoomLevel() != mv.maxZoom)
2241           {
2242             mv.navigationPanel.updateSlider();
2243           }
2244         }
2245         if(callBack)
2246           callBack() ;
2247           
2248         if(mv.overviewmap && mv.overviewmap.submap && mv.overviewmap.submap.mapLayers.length == 0)
2249           mv.overviewmap.addOverviewMapTileLayer();
2250         if(mv.overviewmap && mv.overviewmap.submap)
2251           mv.overviewmap.resetRectangle();
2252         
2253       }
2254     } 
2255     // end of postProcess
2256     MVGlobalVariables.getMapCacheConfig(mapTileLayer, postProcess, this.errorHandler);
2257  }
2258  /**@private*/
2259  MVMapView.prototype.addBaseMapLayer = MVMapView.prototype.addMapTileLayer ;
2260  /**
2261     This methods gets the map tile layer definition object for a given map tile 
2262     layer from the map tile server. 
2263     
2264     The map tile layer must have been registered 
2265     on the MapViewer server side. This method does not return the map tile layer 
2266     definition object directly. The result map tile layer definition is passed
2267     back to the client application as a parameter of a call back function, which
2268     the client application must provide when calling this method. 
2269     Please refer to {@link #addMapTileLayerDefinition} for more information about the
2270     map tile layer definition object.
2271     
2272     @param {Function} callBack is a javascript function that is called after the map tile layer
2273                     definition is fetched from the server side. The map tile layer definition 
2274                     object is passed as the only parameter to this function. 
2275     @param {String} mapTileLayerName mapTileLayerName is a string that identifies the 
2276                     map tile layer. It is defined in the form of data-source-name.map-tile-layer-name, 
2277                     where map-tile-layer-name specifies the name of the map tile 
2278                     layer that has been pre-defined on the server side and 
2279                     data-source-name specifies the name of the MapViewer 
2280                     data source in which the map tile layer is defined. 
2281     @param {String} tileServerURL tileServerURL is a string that specifies the URL
2282                     of the map tile server, which should be in the form
2283                     http://host:port/mapviewer/mcserver. This is an optional parameter. When
2284                     omitted, the map tile server URL is derived from the
2285                     MapViewer base URL specified when creating the MVMapView 
2286                     object. 
2287     @returns        None.
2288     @type void
2289  */
2290  MVMapView.prototype.getMapTileLayerDefinition = function(callBack, mapTileLayerName, tileServerURL)
2291  {
2292    if(!tileServerURL)
2293      tileServerURL = null ;
2294    var mapTileLayer = new MVMapTileLayer(mapTileLayerName, tileServerURL) ;
2295    if (!mapTileLayer.mcsURL)
2296    {
2297      if (this.baseURL)
2298      {
2299        if (MVUtil.strEndWith(this.baseURL, '/'))
2300          mapTileLayer.mcsURL = this.baseURL + 'mcserver';
2301        else
2302          mapTileLayer.mcsURL = this.baseURL + '/mcserver';
2303      }
2304      else
2305      {
2306        MVi18n.reportError("MVMapView.getMapTileLayerDefinition", "MAPVIEWER-05504", null, this.errorHandler);
2307        return ;
2308      }
2309    }
2310    mapTileLayer.mcscfgURL = mapTileLayer.mcsURL;
2311    MVGlobalVariables.getMapCacheConfig(mapTileLayer, callBack, this.errorHandler);
2312  }
2313  
2314  /**
2315    This method removes a map tile layer from the map.
2316    @param {MVMapTileLayer} mapTileLayer the MVMapTileLayer object that 
2317     specifies the map tile layer to be removed.
2318    @returns   None
2319    @type void
2320  */
2321  MVMapView.prototype.removeMapTileLayer = function (mapTileLayer)
2322  {
2323    var i = 0;
2324    var mapSource = mapTileLayer.mapSource;
2325    var mcsURL = mapTileLayer.mcsURL;
2326    if (mapTileLayer.parentLayer){
2327      var parentLayer = mapTileLayer.parentLayer
2328      for (var j=0;j<parentLayer.childrenLayers.length;j++)
2329      {
2330        if (parentLayer.childrenLayers[j] == mapTileLayer)
2331        {
2332          if (parentLayer.childrenLayers.length>1)
2333          {
2334            parentLayer.childrenLayers[j] = parentLayer.childrenLayers[parentLayer.childrenLayers.length-1];
2335            parentLayer.childrenLayers.pop();
2336            //set parentLayer transparent property
2337            var transparent = parentLayer.getTransparent();
2338            if (parentLayer.layerControl)
2339              parentLayer.layerControl.isTransparent = transparent;
2340            parentLayer.refresh(true);
2341            if(this.overviewmap)
2342              this.removeOverviewMapTileLayer(mapSource, mcsURL);
2343            mapTileLayer.parentLayer = null;
2344            return;
2345          }
2346          else
2347          { 
2348            parentLayer.childrenLayers[j] = null;
2349            parentLayer.childrenLayers.pop();
2350            mapTileLayer = parentLayer;
2351            mapTileLayer.parentLayer = null;
2352          }
2353          
2354        }
2355      }
2356    } 
2357    for (; i < this.mapLayers.length; i++)
2358    {
2359      if (this.mapLayers[i] == mapTileLayer)
2360      { 
2361        var tLayer = this.mapLayers[i];
2362        this.mapLayers[i] = this.mapLayers[this.mapLayers.length - 1];
2363        tLayer.destroy();
2364        this.mapLayers.pop();
2365        this.mapLayerNumber-- ;
2366        if(this.overviewmap)
2367          this.removeOverviewMapTileLayer(mapSource, mcsURL);
2368        break ;
2369      }
2370    }
2371    this.showEmbeddedCopyright() ;
2372    if (this.msi.mapSourceName == mapSource && this.mapLayers.length>0)
2373    {
2374      var mv =this;
2375      var lastLayer = this.mapLayers[this.mapLayers.length - 1];
2376      
2377      function AfterSetProvider(redraw)
2378       {
2379         
2380         if (mv.displayed)
2381         {
2382           if(!redraw)
2383           {
2384             if(lastLayer.isExtAPITileLayer())
2385             {
2386               var setExtMapCenter = function(point)
2387               {
2388                 lastLayer.setCenterAndZoomLevel(point.getPointX(), point.getPointY(), mv.zoomLevel) ;
2389               }
2390               var mpoint = MVSdoGeometry.createPoint(mv.mapCenterX, mv.mapCenterY, mv.srid) ;
2391               mv.transformGeom(mpoint, lastLayer.srid, null, setExtMapCenter);
2392             }
2393             else
2394             {
2395               if(lastLayer.layerControl)
2396                 lastLayer.layerControl.initTiles(mv.getPaneWidth(), mv.getPaneHeight(), mv.mapCenterX, mv.mapCenterY);
2397             }
2398           }
2399           else 
2400           {
2401             mv.display() ;
2402           }
2403           if(mv.scalectl)
2404           {
2405             mv.scalectl.update(mv);
2406           }
2407           if (mv.navigationPanel && mv.navigationPanel.getMaxZoomLevel() != mv.maxZoom)
2408           {
2409             mv.navigationPanel.updateSlider();
2410           }
2411         }
2412       }
2413       
2414       this.setProvider(lastLayer,AfterSetProvider);
2415    }
2416  }

2421  */
2422  MVMapView.prototype.removeOverviewMapTileLayer = function(mapSource, mcsURL)
2423  {
2424    //var mcsURL = mapTileLayer.mcsURL;

2426    {

2428      if (overviewMapLayer.mapSource == mapSource && overviewMapLayer.mcsURL == mcsURL)
2429      {
2430        this.overviewmap.submap.removeMapTileLayer(overviewMapLayer);
2431        this.overviewmap.resetRectangle();
2432      }
2433    }
2434  }

2496  {

2531      foi.serverURL = MVGlobalVariables.getDefaultFoiURL() ;
2532    
2533    //============FOI ords calculation ======================//

2619  modified by the application.

2623  {
2624    this.do_GetMinMaxLonLat();
2625    if (this.indFOIsControl != null)
2626    {
2627      var xOffset = (this.indFOIsControl.getLayerWidth() - 
2628                     this.getPaneWidth()) * 0.5 / this.pixPerX;
2629      var yOffset = (this.indFOIsControl.getLayerHeight() - 
2630                     this.getPaneHeight()) * 0.5 /this.pixPerY;
2631      MVUtil.setLeftTop(this.indFOIsControl.getContainer(), 
2632                    (this.getPaneWidth()  - this.indFOIsControl.getLayerWidth())/2, 
2633                    (this.getPaneHeight() - this.indFOIsControl.getLayerHeight())/2);
2634      MVUtil.setLeftTop(this.indFOIsControl.getTopContainer(), 
2635                    (this.getPaneWidth()  - this.indFOIsControl.getLayerWidth())/2, 
2636                    (this.getPaneHeight() - this.indFOIsControl.getLayerHeight())/2);  
2637      this.indFOIsControl.refreshIndFOIs(this.mapWindowMinLon - xOffset, 
2638                   this.mapWindowMinLat - yOffset, this.mapWindowMaxLon + xOffset, 
2639                   this.mapWindowMaxLat + yOffset);
2640    }

2799   * This method disables the marquee zoom tool. 
2800   *@return none

2813  /**
2814   * This method, when invoked, allows user to zoom the map by hand drawing a 
2815   * rectangle on the map. The map center and zoom level is adjusted so that 
2816   * the rectangle area can most closely fill the map. The marquee zoom tool
2817   * can be invoked in one of the following modes:
2818   *<ul>
2819   *<li>"one_time" In this mode, the user can use the marquee zoom tool for only
2820   *               once. After zooming the map by rectangle drawing for the first
2821   *               time, the marquee zoom tool becomes inactive and the user is 
2822   *               no longer able to draw rectangle and zoom the map unless 
2823   *               this method is invoked once again.</li>
2824   *<li>"continuous" In this mode, the user can use the marquee zoom tool to zoom
2825   *               the map by rectangle drawing repeatedly. After each 
2826   *               rectangle drawing and zooming, the user can immediately start
2827   *               drawing another rectangle and zooming the map by clicking and
2828   *               dragging the mouse. The marquee zoom tool stays active until
2829   *               MVMapView.stopMarqueeZoom is invoked.</li>
2830   *<li>"prompt"   In this mode, the user can use the marquee zoom tool to zoom
2831   *               the map by rectangle drawing repeatedly. After each 
2832   *               rectangle drawing, the user needs to click on the rectangle
2833   *               to zoom the map. If the user clicks on the other part of the 
2834   *               map, the rectangle disappears and the map will not be zoomed.
2835   *               The marquee zoom tool stays active until
2836   *               MVMapView.stopMarqueeZoom is invoked.</li>
2837   *</ul>
2838   *<br>
2839   *The style of the marquee zoom rectangle can be specified by parameter rectStyle, an object 
2840   * that may have the following attributes: 
2841   *<ul>
2842   *<li>borderColor  A string that specifies the rectangle border color, e.g, "#FF0000".
2843   *<li>borderWidth  An integer that specifies the width of the rectangle border in pixels.
2844   *<li>borderDashed A boolean that specifies whether to draw dashed(true) or solid(false).
2845   *<li>fillColor    A string that specifies the rectangle fill color, e.g., "#555555".
2846   *<li>fillOpacity  A float number ranging from 0(transparent) to 1(opaque) that specifies the 
2847   *                 rectangle fill opacity.
2848   *</ul>
2849   *<br>
2850   *The following code shows how to create such an object.
2851   *<pre>var rectStyle = new Object() ;
2852   *rectStyle.borderColor = "#00FF00" ;
2853   *rectStyle.borderWidth = 1;
2854   *rectStyle.borderDashed = true ;
2855   *rectStyle.fillColor = "#FF0000" ;
2856   *rectStyle.fillOpacity = 0.5 ;
2857   *</pre>
2858   *@param {String} mode a String that specifies the mode of the marquee zoom tool. It can be
2859                   either "one_time" or "continuous". If omitted, the marquee 
2860                   zoom tool is started in "one_time" mode.
2861   *@param {Object} rectStyle an object that specifies the rectangle style. If omitted, the 
2862                   marquee zoom rectangle is drawn in 1) the default style if this method is 
2863                   invoked for the first time, or 2) the style used previously when invoking 
2864                   this method before.
2865   *@param {int} minRectSize a integer that specifies the minimum effective size of the rectangle 
2866                 in screen pixels. The map is zoomed in only when the user draws a rectangle 
2867                 with both height and width being equal to or larger than the mininum effective 
2868                 size. For example, when minRectSize is 5, a 5x5 rectangle will result in 
2869                 map zooming, while neither a 3x4 nor a 2x10 rectangle will result in map zooming.
2870   *@return none
2871   *@type void  
2872  */
2873  MVMapView.prototype.startMarqueeZoom=function(mode, rectStyle, minRectSize)
2874  {
2875    if(!mode)
2876      mode = "one_time" ;
2877    if(minRectSize && minRectSize>0)
2878      this.minRectSize = minRectSize ;
2879    this.marqueeZoomOn = true ;
2880    this.marqueeZoomMode = mode ;
2881    this.marqueeZoom(rectStyle) ;
2882  }
2883  
2884  /**
2885   @private
2886  */
2887  MVMapView.prototype.marqueeZoom=function(rectStyle)
2888  {
2889    if(!this.marqueeZoomOn)
2890      return ;
2891    this.marqueeRectDone = false ;
2892    this.clearMarqueeRect = false ;
2893    var rectangleTool = this.marqueeZoomRectangleTool ;
2894    if(!rectangleTool)
2895    {
2896     rectangleTool=new MVRectangleTool(null, null);
2897     rectangleTool.setDivFillColor("#555555", 0.3) ;
2898     this.addRectangleTool(rectangleTool);
2899     this.marqueeZoomRectangleTool = rectangleTool ;
2900    }
2901    if(rectStyle)
2902      rectangleTool.setDivStyle(rectStyle) ;
2903    rectangleTool.init();
2904    var zoomFunc=MVUtil.closureWrapper(rectangleTool, function()
2905      {
2906        this.clear() ;
2907        var mbr = null ;
2908        if(this.parent.marqueeRectGeom)
2909          mbr = this.parent.marqueeRectGeom.getMBR() ;
2910        if(mbr && 
2911           (this.marqueeZoomMode == "prompt" || 
2912            Math.abs(mbr[2]-mbr[0])*this.parent.pixPerX >= this.parent.minRectSize && 
2913            Math.abs(mbr[3]-mbr[1])*this.parent.pixPerY >= this.parent.minRectSize))
2914        {
2915          var messageTab = document.getElementById("mv_mrqzm_msg");
2916          if(messageTab)
2917            messageTab.parentNode.removeChild(messageTab) ;
2918          this.parent.zoomToRectangle(this.parent.marqueeRectGeom);
2919        }
2920        /*  this.parent.zoomIn(this.parent.getMouseLocation()) ;
2921        else if()
2922          this.parent.zoomIn(MVSdoGeometry.createPoint(mbr[0], mbr[1], this.parent.srid)) ;
2923        else*/
2924          
2925        if(this.parent.marqueeZoomMode != "one_time")
2926        {
2927          this.parent.marqueeZoom() ;
2928        }
2929      });
2930    var continuousZoomFunc=MVUtil.closureWrapper(rectangleTool, function()
2931      {
2932        this.parent.marqueeRectDone = true ;
2933        this.parent.marqueeRectGeom = rectangleTool.getRectangle() ;
2934        zoomFunc() ;
2935     });
2936    var oneTimeZoomFunc=MVUtil.closureWrapper(rectangleTool, function()
2937      {
2938        this.parent.marqueeRectGeom = rectangleTool.getRectangle() ;
2939        zoomFunc() ;
2940        this.marqueeZoomOn = false ;
2941     });
2942    var rectMouseDown=MVUtil.closureWrapper(rectangleTool, function(evt)
2943      {
2944        this.parent.marqueeRectClicked = true ;
2945        evt = (evt) ? evt : ((window.event) ? event : null);
2946        MVUtil.stopEvent(evt);
2947        
2948      });
2949    var rectMouseUp=MVUtil.closureWrapper(rectangleTool, function(evt)
2950      {
2951        evt = (evt) ? evt : ((window.event) ? event : null);
2952        if(this.parent.marqueeRectClicked)
2953        {
2954          MVUtil.stopEvent(evt);
2955          zoomFunc() ;
2956        }
2957      });
2958    var promptZoomFunc=MVUtil.closureWrapper(rectangleTool, function()
2959      {
2960        this.parent.marqueeRectDone = true ;
2961        this.parent.marqueeRectGeom = rectangleTool.getRectangle() ;
2962        if(!this.parent.marqueeRectGeom)
2963        {
2964          this.clear() ;
2965          this.parent.marqueeZoom() ;
2966          return ;
2967        }
2968        var mv = this.parent ;
2969        var rectDIV = rectangleTool.getRectangleDIV();
2970        MVUtil.setCursor(rectDIV, "crosshair") ;
2971        if(MVi18n.getInfoMessage("marqueeZoomHint"))
2972        {
2973          rectDIV.onmouseover = function(evt)
2974          {
2975            var messageTab = document.getElementById("mv_mrqzm_msg");
2976            if(messageTab)
2977              messageTab.parentNode.removeChild(messageTab) ;
2978            messageTab = MVUtil.createSingleCellTable(MVi18n.getInfoMessage("marqueeZoomHint"));
2979            messageTab.id = "mv_mrqzm_msg" ;
2980            messageTab.style.border="1px solid #000000";
2981            messageTab.style.backgroundColor="#FFFFCC";
2982            messageTab.style.position = "absolute" ;
2983            var mouseLoc = MVUtil.getMouseLeftTop(mv, evt) ;
2984            messageTab.style.left=mouseLoc.x+"px" ;
2985            messageTab.style.top=mouseLoc.y+"px" ;
2986            messageTab.style.zIndex = 9999;
2987            mv.base_div.appendChild(messageTab) ;
2988          };
2989          rectDIV.onmouseout = function()
2990          {
2991            var messageTab = document.getElementById("mv_mrqzm_msg");
2992            if(messageTab)
2993              messageTab.parentNode.removeChild(messageTab) ;
2994          };
2995        }
2996        this.parent.marqueeRectClicked = false ;
2997        rectDIV.onmousedown = rectMouseDown ;
2998        rectDIV.onmouseup = rectMouseUp ;
2999        rectDIV.onclick = function(evt)
3000        {
3001          MVUtil.stopEvent(evt);
3002        };
3003      });
3004    this.marqueeRectClicked = false ;
3005    if(this.marqueeZoomMode == "prompt")
3006      rectangleTool.addEventListener("on_finish", promptZoomFunc);
3007    else if(this.marqueeZoomMode == "continuous")
3008      rectangleTool.addEventListener("on_finish", continuousZoomFunc);
3009    else
3010      rectangleTool.addEventListener("on_finish", oneTimeZoomFunc);
3011  }
3012  
3013   /**
3014   *This method adjusts the map center and zoom level so that the rectangle area 
3015   *specified by an MVSdoGeometry object can best fill the map. 
3016   *@param {MVSdoGeometry} sdoRectangle an MVSdoGeometry object that specifies 
3017   *                       the rectangle area to fill the map.
3018   *@return none
3019   *@type void  
3020   *@requires MVSdoGeometry
3021  */
3022  MVMapView.prototype.zoomToRectangle=function(sdoRectangle)
3023  {
3024    if(!this.displayed)
3025    {
3026      this.delayOperation(this, "zoomToRectangle", sdoRectangle) ;
3027      return ;
3028    }
3029    var mv = this ;
3030    var callBack = function(sdoRectangle)
3031    {
3032     var ords=sdoRectangle.getMBR();
3033     
3034     var width=Math.abs(ords[0]-ords[2]);
3035     var height=Math.abs(ords[1]-ords[3]);
3036         
3037     var widthPx=width*(mv.pixPerX);
3038     var heightPx=height*(mv.pixPerY);
3039         
3040     var paneWidth=mv.getPaneWidth();
3041     var paneHeight=mv.getPaneHeight();
3042         
3043     var zoomLevel = mv.zoomLevel;
3044     var newZoomLevel = zoomLevel;
3045     var maxZoomLevel = mv.maxZoom;
3046         
3047     if(paneWidth<widthPx || paneHeight<heightPx)
3048     {
3049         for (var i=(zoomLevel-1); i>=0; --i)
3050         {
3051           newZoomLevel=i;
3052             
3053           var newPaneWidth=(mv.TileW[i]/mv.msi.getTileWidth(i))*width;
3054           var newPaneHeight=(mv.TileH[i]/mv.msi.getTileHeight(i))*height;
3055             
3056           if(newPaneWidth<=paneWidth && newPaneHeight<=paneHeight)
3057             break;
3058         }
3059     }
3060     else if(paneWidth>widthPx && paneHeight>heightPx)
3061     {
3062         for (var i=(zoomLevel+1); i<=maxZoomLevel; ++i)
3063         {
3064           var newPaneWidth=(mv.TileW[i]/mv.msi.getTileWidth(i))*width;
3065           var newPaneHeight=(mv.TileH[i]/mv.msi.getTileHeight(i))*height;
3066             
3067           if(newPaneWidth<=paneWidth && newPaneHeight<=paneHeight)
3068             newZoomLevel=i;
3069           else
3070             break;
3071         }
3072     }
3073   
3074     var newcx = (ords[0]+ords[2])/2;
3075     var newcy = (ords[1]+ords[3])/2;
3076     var newCenter=MVSdoGeometry.createPoint(newcx, newcy, mv.srid);
3077     mv.zoomTo(newZoomLevel, newCenter);
3078    }
3079    if(!sdoRectangle.srid)
3080      sdoRectangle.srid = this.srid ;
3081    if (sdoRectangle.srid && this.srid != sdoRectangle.srid)
3082      this.transformGeom(sdoRectangle, this.srid, null, callBack);
3083    else
3084      callBack(sdoRectangle) ;
3085  }
3086  /**@private*/
3087  MVMapView.prototype.getThemeBBoxAndSetThemeWindowSize = function(layerControl)
3088  {
3089    var xOffset = (layerControl.getLayerWidth() - this.getPaneWidth()) * 0.5 /this.pixPerX;
3090    var yOffset = (layerControl.getLayerHeight() - this.getPaneHeight()) * 0.5 /this.pixPerY;
3091    var bbox = new Array();
3092    if(layerControl.themebasedfoi.sizeXratio==1 && layerControl.themebasedfoi.sizeYratio==1)
3093    {
3094      bbox[0] = this.mapWindowMinLon;
3095      bbox[1] = this.mapWindowMinLat;
3096      bbox[2] = this.mapWindowMaxLon;
3097      bbox[3] = this.mapWindowMaxLat;
3098    }
3099    else
3100    {
3101      var coordsMin = this.getMeshCoordsMin4ThemeBasedFOIQuery(this.mapWindowMinLon - xOffset, this.mapWindowMinLat - yOffset);
3102      var coordsMax = this.getMeshCoordsMax4ThemeBasedFOIQuery(this.mapWindowMaxLon + xOffset, this.mapWindowMaxLat + yOffset);
3103      bbox[0] = coordsMin.x;
3104      bbox[1] = coordsMin.y;
3105      bbox[2] = coordsMax.x;
3106      bbox[3] = coordsMax.y;
3107    }
3108    var qwidth    = Math.floor((bbox[2] - bbox[0])* this.pixPerX+0.5);
3109    var qheight   = Math.floor((bbox[3] - bbox[1])* this.pixPerY+0.5);
3110    layerControl.setRealSize(qwidth, qheight); 
3111    return bbox ;
3112  }

3114  /**
3115    return true if there is at least one bounding theme
3116    @private
3117  */
3118  MVMapView.prototype.loadBoundingTheme = function()
3119  {
3120    this.do_GetMinMaxLonLat();   
3121    var lc = 0; 
3122    for (lc = 0; lc < this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup.length; lc++)
3123    {
3124      var layer = this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup[lc]; 
3125      if(layer.themebasedfoi.isBoundingTheme)
3126      {
3127        layer.clearTransImageLayer() ;
3128        var themeBBox = this.getThemeBBoxAndSetThemeWindowSize(layer) ;
3129        layer.refreshFOIs(this, themeBBox[0],themeBBox[1],themeBBox[2],themeBBox[3], true, true, null, true, layer.themebasedfoi.recenterOnly);
3130        return true;
3131      }
3132    }
3133    return false ;
3134  }

3158  /**
3159    This method adds a theme-based FOI layer to the map. A theme refers to a 
3160    spatial layer in the database. 
3161    @param {Object}  themeBasedFOI an MVThemeBasedFOI object that defines 
3162     the theme-based FOI layer.
3163    @returns   None
3164    @type void
3165  */
3166  MVMapView.prototype.addThemeBasedFOI = function(themeBasedFOI)
3167  {
3168    if(!this.defaultDataSource && this.compareBaseURL(themeBasedFOI.serverURL) && 
3169       !themeBasedFOI.isJDBCTheme && !themeBasedFOI.isCustomTheme)
3170    {
3171     var sourceArray=themeBasedFOI.theme.split(".");
3172     if (sourceArray.length>=2)
3173     {
3174       MVGlobalVariables.setDefaultDataSource(sourceArray[0]);
3175       this.setDefaultDataSource(sourceArray[0]) ;
3176     }
3177    }
3178    if(this.smoothPanning)
3179    {
3180      this.putThemeIntoSPQueue(themeBasedFOI) ;
3181      return ;
3182    }
3183    
3184    if(!themeBasedFOI)
3185    {
3186      MVi18n.reportError("MVMapView.addThemeBasedFOI", "MAPVIEWER-05519", "themeBasedFOI", this.errorHandler);
3187      return ;
3188    }
3189    if (!this.infoLayer)
3190      this.infoLayer = new MVInfoLayerControl(this, "1");
3191    for (var i = 0; i < this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup.length; i++)
3192    {
3193      if (MVUtil.strTrim(this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup[i].themebasedfoi.name) == MVUtil.strTrim(themeBasedFOI.name))
3194      {
3195        MVi18n.reportError("MVMapView.addThemeBasedFOI", "MAPVIEWER-05509", MVUtil.strTrim(themeBasedFOI.name), this.errorHandler);
3196        return;
3197      }
3198    }
3199    themeBasedFOI.parent = this;
3200 
3201    var layerControl = new MVThemeBasedFOIControl(this, themeBasedFOI);
3202    /*if (this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup.length + 132 < 229)
3203    {
3204      layerControl.div.style.zIndex = this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup.length + 132;
3205      layerControl.origIndex = layerControl.div.style.zIndex - 129;
3206    }*/
3207    layerControl.currentIndex = this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup.length;
3208    if (this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup.length < 100)
3209    {
3210      layerControl.div.style.zIndex = this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup.length*2 + 130;
3211      layerControl.origIndex = this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup.length ;
3212    }
3213    else
3214    {
3215      layerControl.div.style.zIndex = 100*2 + 130;
3216      layerControl.origIndex = 100;
3217    }
3218    layerControl.setSize(parseInt(themeBasedFOI.sizeXratio * (this.getPaneWidth())), 
3219                         parseInt(themeBasedFOI.sizeYratio *(this.getPaneHeight())));
3220    this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup[this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup.length] = layerControl;
3221    if (this.displayed)
3222    {
3223      var themeBBox = this.getThemeBBoxAndSetThemeWindowSize(layerControl) ;
3224      MVUtil.setLeftTop(layerControl.getContainer(), Math.ceil((themeBBox[0] - this.mapWindowMinLon) * this.pixPerX), 
3225                       -Math.ceil((themeBBox[3] - this.mapWindowMaxLat) * this.pixPerY)); 
3226                       
3227      if(themeBasedFOI.isBoundingTheme)
3228       layerControl.refreshFOIs(this,themeBBox[0], themeBBox[1], 
3229                                themeBBox[2], themeBBox[3], false, true, false, false, themeBasedFOI.recenterOnly);
3230      else
3231       layerControl.refreshFOIs(this,themeBBox[0], themeBBox[1], 
3232                                themeBBox[2], themeBBox[3], false, false);                      
3233    }
3234  }

3236  /**
3237    This method gets the current display index of the theme-based FOI layer.
3238    @param {object}  themeBasedFOI themeBasedFOI is the MVThemeBasedFOI object 
3239                     that defines the theme-based FOI layer.
3240    @returns         The theme-based FOI layer index(1-100)
3241    @type int
