5927  /**
5928  @private
5929  */ 
5930  function KeyCodesArray(keyCodes)
5931  {
5932    this.length = 0;
5933    if(keyCodes)
5934    {
5935      for(var i=keyCodes.length-1;i>=0;--i)
5936      {
5937        this.add(keyCodes[i]);
5938        this.length++;   
5939      }    
5940    } 
5941  }
5942  /**
5943  @private
5944  */ 
5945  KeyCodesArray.prototype.add=function(keyCode)
5946  {
5947    if(!this.contains(keyCode))
5948    {
5949      this["key"+keyCode]=1;
5950      this.length++;
5951    }   
5952  }
5953  
5954  /**
5955  @private
5956  */ 
5957  KeyCodesArray.prototype.remove=function(keyCode)
5958  {
5959    if(this.exist(keyCode))
5960    {
5961      delete this["key"+keyCode];
5962      this.length--; 
5963    } 
5964  }
5965  
5966  /**
5967  @private
5968  */ 
5969  KeyCodesArray.prototype.contains=function(keyCode)
5970  {
5971    return this["key"+keyCode]==1;  
5972  }
5973  
5974  /**
5975  @private
5976  */ 
5977  KeyCodesArray.prototype.exist=function(keyCode)
5978  {
5979    return this["key"+keyCode]==1||this["key"+keyCode]==2; 
5980  }
5981  
5982  /**
5983  @private
5984  */ 
5985  KeyCodesArray.prototype.sleep=function()
5986  {
5987    for(prop in this)
5988    {
5989      if(typeof this[prop]!="function")
5990      {
5991        this[prop]=2;   
5992      }   
5993    }    
5994  }
5995  
5996  /**
5997  @private
5998  */ 
5999  KeyCodesArray.prototype.wakeup=function()
6000  {
6001    for(prop in this)
6002    {
6003      if(typeof this[prop]!="function")
6004      {
6005        this[prop]=1;      
6006      }       
6007    }   
6008  }

6010  //========= MapDecoration, Copyright panel,Navigation bar abd scalebar ========
6011  /**
6012    This method adds a MapDecoration object to the map. A map decoration is
6013    a piece of user supplied HTML content (such as a map title string or a custom built
6014    control bar) that can be 
6015    displayed on top of the map. Once added, a map decoration will not move with the map when the map is recentered. 
6016    <p>The map decoration can be set to collapsible so that it can be minimized when
6017    the user clicks on the minimization button. By default, a map decoration is 
6018    not collapsible. </p>
6019    <p>The map decoration can be set to be draggable so that the user can move 
6020    the map decoration inside the map window by dragging it using mouse.
6021    
6022    @param {Object} mapdecoration a MapDecoration object to be displayed on the map
6023    @returns None
6024    @type void
6025  */
6026  MVMapView.prototype.addMapDecoration = function(mapdecoration)
6027  {
6028    if (this.mapDecorationArray == null)
6029      this.mapDecorationArray = new Array();
6030    this.mapDecorationArray.push(mapdecoration);
6031    if (this.displayed)
6032    {
6033      var id = "_md_"+this.mapDecorationId
6034      mapdecoration.init(id,this,this.base_div);
6035      this.mapDecorationId++;
6036      mapdecoration.displayed = true ;
6037      
6038      //add by zhengwan 
6039      //call afterDisAction when the mapdecoration success displayed
6040      if(mapdecoration.afterDisAction)
6041      {
6042         mapdecoration.afterDisAction();
6043      }
6044    }
6045 }
6046  
6047  /**
6048   This method removes a map decoration from the current map.
6049   @param {MVMapDecoration} mapdecoration the MVMapDecoration object to be removed
6050   @returns None
6051   @type void
6052  */
6053  MVMapView.prototype.removeMapDecoration = function (mapdecoration)
6054  {
6055    if (mapdecoration == null || mapdecoration.id == null || this.mapDecorationArray ==null)
6056    {
6057      return;
6058    }  
6059    for (var i=0;i < this.mapDecorationArray.length; i++)
6060      if (this.mapDecorationArray[i].id == mapdecoration.id)
6061      {
6062        if (this.mapDecorationArray[i].isPrintable)
6063          this.printReset();
6064        this.mapDecorationArray[i]  = this.mapDecorationArray[this.mapDecorationArray.length - 1]
6065        this.mapDecorationArray.pop();
6066         mapdecoration.cleanUp();
6067         
6068        var divToBeRemoved = null ;
6069        if (mapdecoration.collapsible)
6070          divToBeRemoved = mapdecoration.contentdiv;
6071        else
6072          divToBeRemoved = mapdecoration.fixedDiv;
6073         
6074        divToBeRemoved.onclick = null;
6075        divToBeRemoved.onmouseover = null;
6076        divToBeRemoved.onmouseout = null;
6077        this.base_div.removeChild(divToBeRemoved);
6078        MVUtil.deleteNode(divToBeRemoved);
6079        this.adjustCopyrightPosition();
6080        break ;
6081     }
6082  }

6086  /**
6087  *This method adds a copyright notice on the bottom right side of the map. By default,
6088  *the copyright node is displayed at the lower-right corner of the map. You can 
6089  *customize its positioning and/or styling by specifying an options object when invoking
6090  *this method. 
6091  *
6092  *<p>The options object can have the following attributes:</p>
6093  *        <UL>
6094  *          <LI>left: This attribute specifies the horizontal position of the copyright node 
6095  *          relative to the upper-left corner from the map. It should be a float number in 
6096  *          the range of 0 to 1. The absolute position in pixels is left*map_window_width + xOffset.</LI>
6097  *          <LI>top: This attribute specifies the vertical position of the copyright node 
6098  *          relative to the upper-left corner from the map. It should be a float number in 
6099  *          the range of 0 to 1. The absolute position in pixels is top*map_window_height + yOffset.</LI>
6100  *          <LI>xOffset: This attribute specifies the horizontal offset in pixels. It should be an integer.</LI>
6101  *          <LI>yOffset: This attribute specifies the vertical offset in pixels. It should be an integer.</LI>
6102  *          <LI>style: This attribute specifies the CSS style of the copyright note. It should be a string, e.g. 
6103  *          "color:#0000FF;font-family:Arial;font-size:12;font-weight:bold".</LI>
6104  *        </UL>
6105 
6106  *<p>You can also specify the font type, color and size of the copyright 
6107  *note by defining your own CSS style. The CSS style must be named .MV_COPYRIGHT. Here is
6108  *an example.</p>
6109  *
6110  *<pre>
6111  *  <style type="text/css">
6112  *    .MV_COPYRIGHT{
6113  *       font-family: Arial; 
6114  *       font-weight:bold;
6115  *       color: #FF0000;
6116  *    }
6117  *  </style>
6118  *</pre>
6119  *
6120  *@param  {string} copyright a string to be displayed as the copyright notice.
6121  *@param  {Object} options an object that specifies positioning and/or styling parameters. 
6122  *@returns   None
6123  *@type void
6124  */
6125  MVMapView.prototype.addCopyRightNote = function(copyright, options)
6126  {
6127    this.userDefinedCopyright = copyright ;
6128    this.showCopyRight(copyright, options) ;
6129  }

6156  function createDIVMarkerNode(parent, _image, _width, _height, _zIndex, _title)
6157  {
6158    this.div = document.createElement("img");
6159    this.div.src = _image ;
6160    this.div.style.position="absolute";
6161    this.div.style.zIndex = _zIndex;
6162    if(_title)
6163     this.div.title = _title; 
6164    this.div.style.width= MVUtil.pixel(_width);
6165    this.div.style.height= MVUtil.pixel(_height);

6171  /**
6172  *This method creates a map navigation panel and places it on the current map. 
6173  *The default navigation panel has a zoom level bar that can be dragged to change 
6174  *map zoom level and 8-direction panning buttons. 
6175  *<p>You can also add the navigation panel by creating a {@link MVNavigationPanel}
6176  * object and adding it to a MVMapDecoration object, which has more control options.
6177  *@param  {string} position that specifies the position of the navigation bar on the map.
6178  *If its value is west (the default), the navigation panel is placed in the upper left side of the map.
6179  *If its value is east, the navigation panel is placed in the upper right side of the map.
6180  *@param  {boolean}panningButtons a boolean that specifies whether to add the panning buttons to the navigation panel.
6181  *@param  {boolean}zoomingBars a boolean that specifies whether to add the zooming bar to the navigation panel.
6182  *@param  {boolean} zoomingButtons a boolean that specifies whether to add the zooming buttons(+/-) to the navigation panel.
6183  *@param  {boolean} zoomLevelBars a boolean that specifies whether to add the zoom level bars to the navigation panel.
6184  *@returns   None
6185  *@type void
6186  */
6187  MVMapView.prototype.addNavigationPanel = function(position, panningButtons, zoomingBars, zoomingButtons, zoomLevelBars)
6188  {
6189    this.navigationPanel = new MVNavigationPanel(panningButtons, zoomingBars, zoomingButtons, zoomLevelBars) ;
6190    if(!position)
6191     position = "WEST" ;
6192    this.navigationPanel.navPosition = position ;
6193    if(this.displayed)
6194     this.navigationPanel.init(this.base_div, this) ;
6195  }

6200  /**
6201  This method adds a scale bar in the current map. The scale bar can be placed
6202  at one of the four corners of the map. For map images rendered in geodetic 
6203  systems, the scale bar is calculated using the Earth (sphere) surface distances. 
6204  For map images rendered in projected systems, by default
6205  the scale bar is calculated using the Cartesian distances in the projected 
6206  system. For better accuracy, user can also tell the map client to calculate 
6207  sphere surface distances by converting projected coordinates to geodetic 
6208  coordinates. 
6209  *<p>You can also add the scale bar by creating a {@link MVScaleBar}
6210  * object and adding it to a MVMapDecoration object, which has more control options.
6211  
6212  @param {int} position An integer between 1-4 that specifies the scale bar position, 
6213               which can be one of the four corners: 
6214               1 - Upper-right; 2 - Lower-left; 3 - Lower-right; 4 - Upper-left.
6215  @param {int} hOffset An integer that specifies the horizontal offset of the scale 
6216               bar relative to the right or left border of the map. If the scale bar
6217               is placed on the right side of the map, hOffset specifies the offset 
6218               relative to the right border. If the scale bar is placed on the left 
6219               side of the map, hOffset specifies the offset relative to the left 
6220               border.
6221  @param {int} vOffset An integer that specifies the vertical offset of the scale bar
6222               relative to the upper or lower border of the map. If the scale bar
6223               is placed on the upper side of the map, vOffset specifies the offset 
6224               relative to the upper border. If the scale bar is placed on the lower 
6225               side of the map, vOffset specifies the offset relative to the lower
6226               border.
6227  @param {boolean}transformToGeodetic optional, this parameter tells the map client
6228               whether to convert the projected coordinates to geodetic coordinates
6229               and calculate the scale bar using sphere surface distances. This 
6230               parameter should be used only for map images rendered in projected 
6231               systems.
6232  @returns   None
6233  @type void
6234  */
6235  MVMapView.prototype.addScaleBar=function(position,hOffset,vOffset,transformToGeodetic)
6236  {
6237    if(this.scalectl)
6238      return ;
6239    this.scalectl = new MVScaleBar(transformToGeodetic) ;
6240    this.scalebarPosition = position || this.scalebarPosition;
6241    this.scalebarOffsetWidth = hOffset || this.scalebarOffsetWidth;
6242    this.scalebarOffsetHeight = vOffset || this.scalebarOffsetHeight;
6243    // delay adding scaleBarControl if map is not initialized
6244    //if(this.msi)
6245    if(this.displayed)   
6246      this.addScaleBarControl(this.scalectl);
6247  }

6249  /**
6250   This method sets the mouse cursor style when the mouse is inside the map 
6251   container and not over any map content other than map tiles.
6252   @param {String} cursorStyle A string that specifies the cursor style to 
6253          be used, which must be one of the standard CSS cursor style names 
6254          such as "crosshair", "pointer" and "move".
6255   @param {String} cursorType A string that specifies when the cursor style
6256          should be used. Its value can be one of the following:
6257          <ul>
6258            <li>
6259             "default" Cursor style to be used when the mouse is on the map 
6260             and no mouse key has been pressed.
6261            </li>
6262            <li>
6263              "dragging" Cursor style to be used when the map is being dragged.
6264            </li>
6265          <ul>
6266   @returns   None
6267   @type void
6268  */
6269  MVMapView.prototype.setMouseCursorStyle = function(cursorStyle, cursorType)
6270  {
6271    if(cursorType=="dragging")
6272      this.cursorStyleDragging = cursorStyle ;
6273    else if(cursorType=="default")
6274    {
6275      this.cursorStyleDefault = cursorStyle ;
6276      this.setTileLayerCursor(cursorStyle);
6277    }
6278  }
6279 /**
6280   This methods enables or disables loading icon. When it is enabled, an animated 
6281   loading icon is displayed whenever the map client starts loading map tiles and 
6282   FOIs. The loading icon disappears when all map tiles and FOIs are loaded.
6283   @param {Boolean} enable a Boolean that specifies whether to enable loading icon,
6284                   true(enable) or false(disable).
6285   @returns   None
6286   @type void
6287 */
6288 MVMapView.prototype.enableLoadingIcon = function(enabled)
6289 {
6290   this.loadingIconEnabled = enabled ;
6291   if(!enabled)
6292     this.setLoadingIconVisible(false) ;
6293 }
6294 /**
6295   This method shows or hides the loading icon. 
6296   @param {Boolean} visible a Boolean that specifies whether to show or hide the loading icon,
6297                   true(show) or false(hide).
6298   @returns   None
6299   @type void
6300 */
6301 MVMapView.prototype.setLoadingIconVisible = function(visible)
6302 {
6303   if(!this.loadingIconEnabled)
6304     visible = false ;
6305   if(!visible)
6306   {
6307     if(this.loadingIcon)
6308       this.loadingIcon.style.visibility = "hidden" ;
6309   }
6310   else
6311   {
6312     if (!this.loadingIcon)
6313     {
6314       var mark = document.createElement("img"); //new Image();
6315       mark.src = MVGlobalVariables.imgFilePath + "loading.gif" ;
6316       mark.style.zIndex = 2001;
6317       mark.style.position = "absolute";
6318       var w=0,h=0;
6319       if(mark.width)
6320         w = mark.width ;
6321       if(mark.height)
6322         h = mark.height;
6323       mark.style.left = MVUtil.pixel((this.getPaneWidth() - w)/2);
6324       mark.style.top = MVUtil.pixel((this.getPaneHeight() - h)/2);
6325       var mv = this;
6326       mark.onload = function()
6327       {
6328         mark.style.left = MVUtil.pixel((mv.getPaneWidth() - mark.width)/2);
6329         mark.style.top = MVUtil.pixel((mv.getPaneHeight() - mark.height)/2);
6330         mark.onload = null ;
6331       };
6332       this.base_div.appendChild(mark);
6333       this.loadingIcon = mark ;
6334     }
6335     else
6336     {
6337       this.loadingIcon.style.left = MVUtil.pixel((this.getPaneWidth() - this.loadingIcon.width)/2);
6338       this.loadingIcon.style.top = MVUtil.pixel((this.getPaneHeight() - this.loadingIcon.height)/2);
6339       this.loadingIcon.style.visibility = "visible" ;
6340     }
6341   }
6342 } 
6343 /**
6344   This method converts the location specified by the screen coordinates to the cooresponding location
6345   in the map coordinate system. The screen coordinates are specified as the screen space offsets from 
6346   the upper-left corner of the map window. 
6347   @param {Object} screenXY the screen coordinates specified as an object with x and y attributes.
6348   @returns  MVSdoGeometry
6349   @type  MVSdoGeometry
6350 */
6351 MVMapView.prototype.getMapCoordinates = function(screenXY)
6352 {
6353   return MVSdoGeometry.createPoint(screenXY.x/this.pixPerX+this.mapWindowMinLon,
6354                                    this.mapWindowMaxLat-screenXY.y/this.pixPerY,this.srid);
6355 }
6356 /**
6357   This method sets the image format and background color to be used to render 
6358   FOI images. 
6359   <p>The image format can be either png8 or png24. Png8 is faster especially
6360   with IE, but it only supports 256 colors and does not support semi-transparency. 
6361   Png24 supports semi-transparency and much richer colors. The default FOI 
6362   image format is png24. </p>
6363   
6364   <p>The default FOI image format set by this method can be overwritten by 
6365   {@link MVFOI#setImageFormat} and {@link MVThemeBasedFOI#setImageFormat}.</p>
6366   
6367   @param {String} format the default FOI image format.
6368   @returns None
6369   @type void
6370 */
6371 MVMapView.prototype.setDefaultFOIImageFormat = function(format)
6372 {
6373   if(format)
6374     this.foiImageFormat = format.toUpperCase() ;
6375 }
6376 /**
6377   This method sets the instance specific error handler. Only errors that happen
6378   to this MVMapView instance are handled by the error handler specified by
6379   this method. 
6380   
6381   <p>The error handler is 
6382   a javascript function that is called whenever an error occurs. The error message 
6383   is passed to error handler as the only parameter. By default, the error handler 
6384   is "alert", which means a browser alert message window is displayed whenever 
6385   an error occurs. </p>
6386   
6387   @param {Function} errorHandler the javascript function to handle errors.
6388   @returns   None
6389   @type void
6390 */
6391 MVMapView.prototype.setErrorHandler = function(errorHandler)
6392 {
6393   this.errorHandler = errorHandler;
6394 }

6396 /******************************************************************/
6397 /**@private- Check whether all the layers have been loaded.*/  
6398 MVMapView.prototype.checkLayersAndSetLoadingIcon = function()
6399 {
6400   var loaded = true ;
6401   for (var i = 0; i < this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup.length; i++)
6402   {
6403     var layer = this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup[i];     
6404     if(layer.div && layer.isVisible() && layer.loading)
6405     {
6406       loaded = false ;
6407       break ;
6408     }
6409   }
6410   if (loaded && this.foiGroupArray)
6411   {
6412     for(var i=0; i<this.foiGroupArray.length; i++)
6413     {
6414       var group = this.foiGroupArray[i];
6415       if (group.loading)
6416       {
6417         loaded = false;
6418         break;
6419       }
6420     }
6421   }
6422   if(loaded)
6423     this.setLoadingIconVisible(false) ;
6424 }
6425 
6426 /**@private 
6427    Put the theme based foi into a queue and wait for the smooth panning is finished
6428    before adding the theme based foi.
6429  */
6430 MVMapView.prototype.putThemeIntoSPQueue = function(themeBasedFOI)
6431 {
6432   if(!this.spQueue)
6433     this.spQueue = new Array() ;
6434   this.spQueue.push(themeBasedFOI) ;
6435   var mv = this ;
6436   var checkSPQueue = function()
6437   {
6438     if(mv.smoothPanning)
6439       return ;
6440     clearInterval(mv.spIntervalId) ;
6441     mv.spIntervalId = null ;
6442     while(mv.spQueue.length>0)
6443     {
6444       mv.addThemeBasedFOI(mv.spQueue.shift()) ;
6445     }
6446   }
6447   if(!this.spIntervalId)
6448     this.spIntervalId = setInterval(checkSPQueue, 50) ;
6449 }

6451 MVMapView.prototype.setDefaultDataSource = function(ds)
6452 {
6453   if(!this.defaultDataSource)
6454     this.defaultDataSource = ds ;
6455 }
6456 /**@private*/
6457 MVMapView.prototype.compareBaseURL = function(url)
6458 {
6459   if(url && url!="" && url.indexOf(this.baseURL)<0)
6460     return false ;
6461   else
6462     return true ;
6463 }
6464 /**@private*/
6465 MVMapView.prototype.checkSize = function()
6466 {
6467   clearTimeout(this.sizeCheckingHandle);
6468   /*if(!this.oldPaneWidth)
6469   {
6470     document.getElementById("message").innerHTML += "0 oldPaneWidth" ;
6471     this.oldPaneWidth = this.getPaneWidth() ;
6472   }
6473   if(!this.oldPaneHeight)
6474   {
6475     document.getElementById("message").innerHTML += "0 oldPaneHeight" ;
6476     this.oldPaneHeight = this.getPaneHeight() ;
6477   }*/
6478   if(!this.base_div)
6479     return ;
6480   if(Math.abs(this.oldPaneWidth-this.getPaneWidth())>3 ||
6481      Math.abs(this.oldPaneHeight-this.getPaneHeight())>3)
6482   {
6483     this.sizeChanging = true ;
6484     this.sizeStaticTime = 0.4 ;
6485     this.oldPaneWidth = this.getPaneWidth() ;
6486     this.oldPaneHeight = this.getPaneHeight() ;
6487   }
6488   else
6489     this.sizeStaticTime += 0.4 ;
6490   if(this.sizeStaticTime>0.4 && this.sizeChanging)
6491   {
6492     this._mapResized();
6493     this.sizeChanging = false ;
6494     this.sizeStaticTime = 0 ;
6495   }
6496   this.sizeCheckingHandle = this.setTimeout("this.checkSize()", 300) ;
6497 }
6498 /**@private*/
6499 MVMapView.prototype.getScreenXY = function(x, y)
6500 {
6501   return {x: (x-this.mapCenterX)*this.pixPerX + this.getPaneWidth()/2, 
6502           y: (this.mapCenterY-y)*this.pixPerY + this.getPaneHeight()/2};
6503 }

6529 /**@private*/
6530 MVMapView.prototype.delayOperation = function()
6531 {
6532   if(arguments.length<2)
6533     return ;
6534   var paramArray = new Array() ;
6535   for(var i=2; i<arguments.length; i++)
6536     paramArray[i-2] = arguments[i] ;
6537   var oper = {obj:arguments[0], func:arguments[1], params:paramArray};
6538   this.delayedOperations.push(oper);
6539 }
6540  
6541  /************ Static variables and functions *************/
6542  /**
6543   This method adds an map tile layer configuration entry to the map client. The map 
6544   configuration entry is specified by a javascript map configuration object. 
6545   It contains information needed by the map client to assemble and display
6546   map tiles. It defines map tile layer name, map coordinate system, zoom levels
6547   and tiling rules, etc. 
6548   
6549   <p>If the map tile layer configuration is added to the map client using this method,
6550   the same map tile layer configuration will not be fetched from the server. In other 
6551   words, using this method, the application can overwrite the map tile layer
6552   configuration defined on the server side.</p>
6553   
6554   <p>Here is an example.</p>
6555   <pre>
6556    var mapConfig = {
6557          mapTileLayer:"custom_map",
6558          format:"PNG",
6559          coordSys:{srid:8307,type:"GEODETIC",distConvFactor:0.0,
6560                    minX:-180.0,minY:-90.0,maxX:180.0,maxY:90.0},
6561          zoomLevels:
6562          [
6563           {zoomLevel:0,name:"level0", 
6564            tileWidth:61.14411263390067, tileHeight:61.14411263390067,
6565            tileImageWidth:256,tileImageHeight:256},
6566           {zoomLevel:1,name:"level1",
6567            tileWidth:30.572056316950334,tileHeight:30.572056316950334,
6568            tileImageWidth:256,tileImageHeight:256},
6569           {zoomLevel:2,name:"level2",
6570            tileWidth:15.286028158107968,tileHeight:15.286028158107968,
6571            tileImageWidth:256,tileImageHeight:256},
6572           {zoomLevel:3,name:"level3",
6573            tileWidth:4.961746909541633,
6574            tileHeight:4.961746909541633,
6575            tileImageWidth:256,tileImageHeight:256},
6576           {zoomLevel:4,name:"level4",
6577            tileWidth:1.6105512127664132,tileHeight:1.6105512127664132,
6578            tileImageWidth:256,tileImageHeight:256},
6579           {zoomLevel:5,name:"level5",
6580            tileWidth:0.5227742142726501,tileHeight:0.5227742142726501,
6581            tileImageWidth:256,tileImageHeight:256},
6582           {zoomLevel:6,name:"level6",
6583            tileWidth:0.16968897570090388,tileHeight:0.16968897570090388,
6584            tileImageWidth:256,tileImageHeight:256},
6585          ]
6586        }; 
6587      
6588   </pre> 
6589   
6590   <UL>
6591   <LI>Attribute "dataSource" specifies the name of the data source where the map 
6592   tile layer configuration is defined. This attribute can be omitted if 
6593   the map tile layer configuration is defined for a custom map tiles layer.</LI>
6594   <LI>Attribute "mapTileLayer" specifies the name of the map tile layer or custom 
6595   map tiles layer.</LI>
6596   <LI>Attribute "format" specifies tile image format.<LI>
6597   <LI>Attribute "coordSys" specifies the map coordinate system, which is specified 
6598   as an object with the following attributes.
6599     <UL>
6600       <LI>Attribute "srid" specifies the spatial reference ID of the coordinate system.</LI>
6601       <LI>Attribute "type" specifies the type of the coordinate system, which 
6602           can be "GEODETIC", "PROJECTED" or "LOCAL"</LI>
6603       <LI>Attribute "distConvFactor" specifies the distance unit conversion factor
6604           that can be used to convert distance specified in coordinate system 
6605           units into distance specified in meters. 
6606           distConvFactor * [distance in coordinate system units] = [distance in meters]
6607           It should be set to 0 if the direct/linear distance conversion is not 
6608           feasible, e.g., all "GEODETIC" coordinate systems. </LI>
6609       <LI>Attribute "minX" specifies the lower X bound of the coordinate system, 
6610           which should be the minimum X coordinate value of left-most tiles 
6611           in the map coordinate system.</LI>
6612       <LI>Attribute "minY" specifies the lower Y bound of the coordinate system, 
6613           which should be the minimum Y coordinate value of the bottom-most tiles 
6614           in the map coordinate system.</LI>
6615       <LI>Attribute "maxX" specifies the upper X bound of the coordinate system,
6616           which should be the maximum X coordinate value of the right-most tiles 
6617           in the map coordinate system.</LI>
6618       <LI>Attribute "maxY" specifies the upper Y bound of the coordinate system, 
6619           which should be the maximum Y coordinate value of the top-most tiles 
6620           in the map coordinate system.</LI>
6621     </UL>
6622   </LI>
6623   <LI>Attribute "zoomLevels" specifies the predefined zoom levels with tiling rules,
6624   which is specifies as an array. Each element of this array specifies the defintion
6625   of one zoom level. The zoom levels are ordered from level 0 to level n-1, where 
6626   level 0 is the most zoomed out level and level n-1 is the most zoomed in level.
6627   Each zoom level element is specified as an object with the following attributes.
6628     <UL>
6629       <LI>Attribute "zoomLevel" specifies zoom level number. </LI>
6630       <LI>Attribute "name" specifies the name of the zoom level.</LI>
6631       <LI>Attribute "tileWidth" specifies the width of the map tile defined 
6632           in map coordinate system units.</LI>
6633       <LI>Attribute "tileHeight" specifies the height of the map tile defined 
6634           in map coordinate system units.</LI>
6635       <LI>Attribute "tileImageWidth" specifies the width of the map tile image
6636           in screen pixels.</LI>
6637       <LI>Attribute "tileImageHeight" specifies the height of the map tile image
6638           in screen pixels.</LI>
6639     </UL>
6640   </LI>   
6641   </UL>
6642   */
6643  MVMapView.addMapTileLayerDefinition = function(definition)
6644  {
6645    var mcName = definition.dataSource ? definition.dataSource+"."+definition.mapTileLayer:definition.mapTileLayer ;
6646    if(definition)
6647      MVGlobalVariables.addMapCacheConfig(mcName, definition)
6648  }
6649  /**@private*/
6650  MVMapView.XMLHTTPEnabled = false ;
6651  /**
6652   This method sets whether to use browser built-in XMLHttpRequest/XMLHTTP objects 
6653   to communicate with cross domain remote servers for map and FOI requests. 
6654   
6655   <p>Web browsers usually 
6656   do not allow cross-domain AJAX calls, which are remote calls made with 
6657   XMLHttpRequest/XMLHTTP objects to a remote server in a domain different from the 
6658   domain where the application web pages are hosted. This requires that all map and 
6659   FOI requests sent from application web pages must be sent to a MapViewer instance 
6660   in the same domain, which might be inconvienient or even infeasible for some 
6661   applications. With Oracle Maps, cross domain remote map and FOI requests can be 
6662   sent in two different ways: with XMLHttpRequest/XMLHTTP objects enabled or 
6663   disabled. By default, XMLHttpRequest/XMLHTTP objects are disabled when accessing
6664   cross domain remote servers.</p>
6665   
6666   <p>When XMLHttpRequest/XMLHTTP objects are enabled, cross domain requests are sent 
6667   via a proxy server that runs in the application local domain and can forward map 
6668   and FOI requests to any remote server. The proxy server is provided as part of 
6669   MapViewer and must be deployed in the application local domain. When XMLHttpRequest/XMLHTTP 
6670   objects are disabled, cross-domain remote map and FOI requests are sent without 
6671   using XMLHttpRequest/XMLHTTP objects and therefore can be sent direclty to any 
6672   remote server in any domain without going through any proxy. </p>
6673   
6674   <p>When being sent using browser built-in XMLHttpRequest/XMLHTTP objects, remote 
6675   requests can be send in both asynchronous and synchronous mode. When being sent
6676   without using XMLHttpRequest/XMLHTTP objects, remote requests can be sent only
6677   in asynchronous mode. In synchronous mode, the application Javascript code that 
6678   follows the Oracle Maps Javascript client code that initiates the remote request 
6679   is not executed until the remote request is sent and the response is received 
6680   from the remote server. In asynchronous mode, the same application code is always 
6681   executed immediately after the remote request is sent even before the response
6682   from the remote server is received. This can be problemetic when the application
6683   code needs to wait for the outcome of the remote request/response. To properly 
6684   handle such situation, the application should pass a call back function to all 
6685   Oracle Maps client API methods that make remote AJAX calls and pass result 
6686   back to the application. The call back function is called once the response is
6687   received from the server and should implement the application logic that consumes
6688   the result returned from the remote server. The call back function can be used
6689   for both synchronous and asynchronous remote reqeusts. Here is the list of all 
6690   such Oracle Maps client API methods.<p>
6691   <ul>
6692   <li>MVMapView.transformGeom<br>
6693       This method invokes remote server side function to perform coordinate system
6694       transformation.</li>
6695   <li>MVSdoGeometry.getLength<br>
6696       This method invokes remote server side function to calculate the length
6697       of a geometry.</li>
6698   <li>MVSdoGeometry.getArea<br>
6699       This method invokes remote server side function to calculate the area of a
6700       geometry.</li>
6701   </ul>
6702   
6703   @param {Boolean} enable A boolean that specifies whether to enable XMLHttpRequest/XMLHTTP
6704          objects. Its value can be "true"(enable) or "false"(disable).
6705   @returns   None
6706   @type void
6707  */
6708  MVMapView.enableXMLHTTP = function(enable)
6709  {
6710    MVMapView.XMLHTTPEnabled = enable ;
6711  }
6712  
6713  /**
6714   This method gets whether browser built-in XMLHttpRequest/XMLHTTP objects 
6715   are enabled for cross domain requests.  
6716   
6717   @returns true if XMLHttpRequest/XMLHTTP objects are enabled  
6718   @type Boolean
6719   @see #enableXMLHTTP
6720  */
6721  MVMapView.isXMLHTTPEnabled = function()
6722  {
6723    return MVMapView.XMLHTTPEnabled ;
6724  }
6725   /**
6726   This method sets the path of the proxy server, which is relative to the application 
6727   domain. When browser built-in XMLHTTP/XMLHttpRequest is enabled, the map client will 
6728   send all AJAX map and FOI requests to the cross domain map tile  and foi servers 
6729   through the proxy server. The proxy server must be running inside the same domain where 
6730   the application is running. 
6731   
6732   <p>Take the application with a URL like http://host:port/application_context/application_page for 
6733   an example, the application domain is host:port, the context root path of the application 
6734   is application_context. The proxy server must be running inside 
6735   the same domain and its URL should be something like http://host:port/proxy_context/proxy_server_name,
6736   where proxy_context is the context root of the proxy server and proxy_server_name is
6737   the name of the proxy server. The relative path of the proxy server is /proxy_context/proxy_server_name.
6738   The default path of the proxy server is /mapviewer/proxy, which points to the proxy
6739   server shipped with MapViewer.</p>
6740   
6741   @param {String} proxyPath a String the specifies the relative path of the proxy server
6742          objects. Its value can be "true"(enable) or "false"(disable).
6743   @returns   None
6744   @type void
6745   @see #enableXMLHTTP
6746  */
6747  MVMapView.setProxyPath = function(proxyPath)
6748  {
6749    MVGlobalVariables.proxyPath = proxyPath ;
6750  }
6751  
6752  /**
6753   This method sets the global error handler that is invoked when an error occurs. 
6754   
6755   <p>Error handler specified by this method is a global error handler. It is 
6756   invoked only when there is no instance specific error handler defined.</p>
6757    
6758   <p>An error handler is a javascript function which is called when an error occurs. 
6759   The error message is passed to the error handler as the only parameter. 
6760   By default, the error handler is "alert", which means a browser alert 
6761   message window is displayed whenever an error occurs. </p>
6762   
6763   @param {Function} errorHandler the javascript function to handle errors.
6764   @returns   None
6765   @type void
6766  */
6767  MVMapView.setErrorHandler = function(errorHandler)
6768  {
6769    MVi18n.addBehavior("func", errorHandler, "text");
6770  }

6796 /**@private*/
6797 MVMapView.debug = false ;
6798 /**@private
6799   This method enables the debug mode. When in debug mode, the client outputs debugging 
6800   information during runtime. The debug information is displayed using the error handler 
6801   set in {@link #setErrorHandler}. By default, the debug information is displayed
6802   as alert message. However, displaying debug information as alert message interrupts
6803   normal application execution, which might be undesirble oftentimes. If that's the case,
6804   you can create an error handler that displays text info in a less disturbing way, e.g.,
6805   a handler that displays the text info inside a text area on the same web page. Here is
6806   an example.
6807 
6808   ...
6809   function myErrorHandler(info)  
6810   {
6811     document.getElementById("message").innerHTML += '<br>'+info ;
6812   }
6813   MVMapView.setErrorHandler(myErrorHandler) ;
6814   MVMapView.enableDebugMode(true);
6815   ...
6816   <div id="message" style="width:100%;height:100px;overflow:auto">Debug Info:</div>
6817   ...
6818   
6819   @param {Function} errorHandler the javascript function to handle errors.
6820   @returns   None
6821   @type void
6822 */
6823 MVMapView.enableDebugMode = function(enabled)
6824 {
6825   MVMapView.debug = enabled;
6826 }
6827 /**@private*/
6828 MVMapView.transformOrdinates = function(transFunc, inputOrdinates, errorHandler)
6829 {
6830   var ordinates = new Array(inputOrdinates.length);
6831   for(var i=0; i<inputOrdinates.length; i+=2)
6832   {
6833     var result = transFunc(inputOrdinates[i],inputOrdinates[i+1], errorHandler) ;
6834     ordinates[i] = result.x ;
6835     ordinates[i+1] = result.y ;
6836   }
6837   return ordinates ;
6838 }

6840  /**
6841  This method calculate pixels per X unit
6842  */
6843  MVMapView.prototype.getPixelsPerXUnit = function()
6844  {
6845    var tileImageWidth = this.msi.mapConfig.zoomLevels[this.zoomLevel].tileImageWidth;
6846    var tileWidth = this.msi.mapConfig.zoomLevels[this.zoomLevel].tileWidth;
6847    return tileImageWidth / tileWidth ; 
6848  }
6849  
6850  /**
6851  This method calculate pixels per Y unit
6852  */
6853  MVMapView.prototype.getPixelsPerYUnit = function()
6854  {
6855    var tileImageHeight = this.msi.mapConfig.zoomLevels[this.zoomLevel].tileImageHeight;
6856    var tileHeight = this.msi.mapConfig.zoomLevels[this.zoomLevel].tileHeight; 
6857    return tileImageHeight / tileHeight ; 
6858  }

6862 /**@private*/
6863 /**
6864  This method calculate the map is wrap-around in curren map window
6865  */
6866 MVMapView.prototype.wrapAroundLayer = function(layerwidth)
6867 {
6868   if (!layerwidth)
6869     return false;
6870   if (this.wraparound)
6871   {
6872     this.do_GetMinMaxLonLat();
6873     var xOffset = (layerwidth - 
6874                     this.getPaneWidth()) * 0.5 / this.pixPerX;
6875     var minx = this.mapWindowMinLon - xOffset;
6876     var maxx = this.mapWindowMaxLon + xOffset;
6877     
6878     var bbminx = this.msi.coverMinX;
6879     var bbmaxx = this.msi.coverMaxX;
6880     var bbx=bbmaxx-bbminx;
6881     var n=0;
6882     if (minx<bbminx)
6883     {
6884       n=Math.ceil((bbminx-minx)/bbx);
6885       minx+=bbx*n;
6886       maxx+=bbx*n;
6887       n=0-n;
6888     }
6889     else if(minx>bbmaxx)
6890     {
6891       n=Math.ceil((minx-bbmaxx)/bbx);
6892       minx-=bbx*n;
6893       maxx-=bbx*n;
6894     }
6895     if (maxx>bbmaxx)   
6896       return true;
6897     
6898   }
6899   return false
6900 }

6902 /**
6903    This method sets whether to display the map in the wrap-around manner. When the map is 
6904    displayed in such manner, the map wraps around the map space boundray horizontally and 
6905    therefor can be scrolled endlessly horizontally. 
6906 
6907    <p>All vector theme types, except heatmap theme, can be displayed as a theme based FOI layer in wrap-around mode. </p>
6908    
6909    @param {boolean} enable a boolean value which indicates the map should be displayed in wrap-around manner or not
6910    @returns  None
6911    @type     void
6912 */ 
6913 MVMapView.prototype.enableMapWrapAround = function(enable)
6914 {
6915   this.wraparound = enable;
6916 }
6917 MVMapView.extAPITileLayerCount = 0 ;
6918 /**@private
6919   This function adds a external API map tile layer to the map. External API map 
6920   tile layers are placed on the bottom of the map container, which means they
6921   are beneath all native map tile layers. 
6922   
6923   This function creates a map div container for the external API tile layer and
6924   add it into the div container dedicated to external API tile layers.
6925 */
6926 MVMapView.prototype.addExternalAPITileLayer = function(mapTileLayer, callBack)
6927 {
6928   if(!mapTileLayer)
6929     return ;
6930   this.mapLayers.push(mapTileLayer) ;
6931   // Create a DIV to hold the new tile layer
6932   var tileLayerDIV = document.createElement("div") ;
6933   this.base_div.appendChild(tileLayerDIV);
6934   if(!mapTileLayer.visible)
6935     tileLayerDIV.style.visibility = "hidden" ;
6936   tileLayerDIV.style.zIndex=this.mapLayers.length;
6937   tileLayerDIV.style.position="absolute" ;
6938   tileLayerDIV.style.zIndex=1 ;
6939   tileLayerDIV.style.left=MVUtil.pixel(0);
6940   tileLayerDIV.style.top=MVUtil.pixel(0);
6941   tileLayerDIV.style.width="100%" ;
6942   tileLayerDIV.style.height="100%" ;
6943   // Add a transparent image to the tile layer DIV to block any mouse interaction 
6944   // from reaching to the external map layer
6945   var transImage = document.createElement("img");
6946   transImage.src = MVGlobalVariables.imgFilePath + "transparent."+(MVGlobalVariables.browser=="IF"?"gif":"png") ;
6947   transImage.style.position="absolute";
6948   transImage.style.zIndex = 9999;
6949   transImage.style.left = MVUtil.pixel(0);
6950   transImage.style.top = MVUtil.pixel(0);
6951   transImage.style.width = "100%";
6952   transImage.style.height = "100%";
6953   tileLayerDIV.appendChild(transImage) ;
6954   var mv = this ;
6955   tileLayerDIV.ondblclick = function( _event )
6956   {
6957     return mv.mDbClick( _event );
6958   };
6959   // Create the DIV that is going to used by the external API 
6960   var div = document.createElement("div") ;
6961   mapTileLayer.layerDiv = div ;
6962   div.id = "mvexttl_"+MVMapView.extAPITileLayerCount++;
6963   div.style.position="absolute" ;
6964   div.style.left=MVUtil.pixel(0);
6965   div.style.top=MVUtil.pixel(0);
6966   div.style.width="100%" ;
6967   div.style.height="100%" ;
6968   tileLayerDIV.appendChild(div);
6969   if(this.displayed)
6970   {
6971     mapTileLayer.setCenterAndZoomLevel(this.mapCenterX, this.mapCenterY, this.zoomLevel, true) ;
6972     mapTileLayer.init(div) ;
6973   }
6974   mapTileLayer.parent = this ;
6975   MVMapView.addMapTileLayerDefinition(mapTileLayer.tileLayerDefinition) ;
6976 }
6977 /**@private
6978   This function moves the external API tile layer by certain offsets in screen
6979   pixels. It invokes the move method of the external API tile layer object to
6980   move the tile layer if the move method exists. Otherwise, it invokes the 
6981   setCenter method to move the tile layer.
6982   @param xOffset x offset in pixels.
6983   @param yOffset y offset in pixels.
6984   @param x map center X.
6985   @param y map center Y.
6986  */
6987 MVMapView.prototype.moveExternalAPITileLayers = function(xOffset, yOffset, x, y)
6988 {
6989   for(var i=0; i<this.mapLayers.length; i++)
6990   {
6991     var mapTileLayer = this.mapLayers[i] ;
6992     if(mapTileLayer.isExtAPITileLayer() && mapTileLayer.isVisible())
6993     {
6994       if(mapTileLayer.move)
6995         mapTileLayer.move(xOffset, yOffset);
6996       else
6997       {
6998         var setMapCenter = function(point)
6999         {
7000           mapTileLayer.setCenter(point.getPointX(), point.getPointY()) ;
7001         }
7002         var mpoint = MVSdoGeometry.createPoint(x, y, this.srid) ;
7003         this.transformGeom(mpoint, mapTileLayer.srid, null, setMapCenter);
7004       }
7005     }
7006   }
7007 }
7008 /**@private 
7009   This function set the center and zoom level of an external API tile layers.
7010   
7011   @param x map center X.
7012   @param y map center Y.
7013   @param zoomLevel zoom level.
7014   @param setValuesOnly true if only need to set the x, y and zoom level parameter 
7015          values for the tile layer without actually changing the map state.
7016  */
7017 MVMapView.prototype.setExternalAPITileLayerCenter = function(mapTileLayer, x, y, zoomLevel, setValuesOnly)
7018 {
7019   if(!mapTileLayer.isVisible() && !setValuesOnly)
7020     return ;
7021   var setExtMapCenter = function(point)
7022   {
7023     if(setValuesOnly)
7024     {
7025       mapTileLayer.centerX = point.getPointX() ;
7026       mapTileLayer.centerY = point.getPointY() ;
7027       if(zoomLevel!=undefined && zoomLevel!=null)
7028         mapTileLayer.zoomLevel = zoomLevel ;
7029     }
7030     else
7031     {
7032       if(mapTileLayer.map)
7033       {
7034         if(zoomLevel!=undefined && zoomLevel!=null)
7035         {
7036           mapTileLayer.resize();
7037           mapTileLayer.setCenterAndZoomLevel(point.getPointX(), point.getPointY(), zoomLevel) ;
7038         }
7039         else
7040         {
7041           mapTileLayer.setCenter(point.getPointX(), point.getPointY()) ;
7042         }
7043       }
7044       else
7045       {
7046         mapTileLayer.centerX = point.getPointX() ;
7047         mapTileLayer.centerY = point.getPointY() ;
7048         if(zoomLevel!=undefined && zoomLevel!=null)
7049           mapTileLayer.zoomLevel = zoomLevel ;
7050         mapTileLayer.init(mapTileLayer.layerDiv);
7051       }
7052     }
7053   }
7054   var mpoint = MVSdoGeometry.createPoint(x, y, this.srid) ;
7055   this.transformGeom(mpoint, mapTileLayer.srid, null, setExtMapCenter);
7056 }
7057 /**@private
7058   This function set the center and zoom level of all external API tile layers.
7059   
7060   @param x map center X.
7061   @param y map center Y.
7062   @param zoomLevel zoom level.
7063   @param setValuesOnly true if only need to set the x, y and zoom level parameter 
7064          values for the tile layer without actually changing the map state.
7065  */
7066 MVMapView.prototype.setExternalAPITileLayersCenter = function(x, y, zoomLevel, setValuesOnly)
7067 {
7068   for(var i=0; i<this.mapLayers.length; i++)
7069   {
7070     var mapTileLayer = this.mapLayers[i] ;
7071     if(mapTileLayer.isExtAPITileLayer())
7072       this.setExternalAPITileLayerCenter(mapTileLayer, x, y, zoomLevel, setValuesOnly) ;
7073   }
7074 }
7075 /**@private*/
7076 MVMapView.prototype.get1stMapTileLayer = function()
7077 {
7078   if(this.mapLayers.length>0)
7079     return this.mapLayers[0] ;
7080   else
7081     return null ;
7082 }
7083 /**@private 
7084   This function checks the map div left and top to see whether the map goes beyond 
7085   CS boundary. If so, adjust the map div left and top to make sure the map lies
7086   within the cs boundary. This method is called when the map div is being moved.
7087 */
7088 MVMapView.prototype.checkMapDivLeftTop = function(origLeft, divLeft, origTop, divTop)
7089 {
7090   var left, top;
7091   if(this.wraparound || this.overview || !this.enforceCSBound)
7092     return {left:divLeft, top:divTop};
7093     
7094   if(origLeft==divLeft)
7095     left = divLeft;
7096   else
7097   {
7098     var offsetX = (origLeft-divLeft)/this.pixPerX ;
7099     var ltr = (origLeft < divLeft) ;
7100     
7101     var csMinX = this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.minX;
7102     var csMaxX = this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.maxX;
7103     var csCenterX = (this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.minX+this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.maxX)/2;
7104     var csWidth = this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.maxX-this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.minX;
7105     var mapWidth = this.mapWindowMaxLon-this.mapWindowMinLon;
7106     var newCenterX = this.mapCenterX+offsetX ;
7107     var newMapMinX = newCenterX - mapWidth/2 ;
7108     var newMapMaxX = newCenterX + mapWidth/2 ;
7109     if(ltr)
7110     {
7111       if(newMapMinX < csMinX)
7112       {
7113         if(mapWidth > csWidth)
7114         {
7115           if(newCenterX < csCenterX)
7116             newCenterX = csCenterX ;
7117         }
7118         else
7119         {
7120           if(this.mapWindowMinLon < csMinX)
7121             newCenterX = this.mapCenterX ;
7122           else
7123             newCenterX = newCenterX - (newMapMinX-csMinX) ;
7124         }
7125       }
7126     } 
7127     else
7128     {
7129       if(newMapMaxX > csMaxX)
7130       {
7131         if(mapWidth > csWidth)
7132         {
7133           if(newCenterX > csCenterX)
7134             newCenterX = csCenterX ;
7135         }
7136         else
7137         {
7138           if(this.mapWindowMaxLon > csMaxX)
7139             newCenterX = this.mapCenterX ;
7140           else
7141             newCenterX = newCenterX - (newMapMaxX-csMaxX) ;
7142         }
7143       }
7144     }
7145     offsetX = newCenterX - this.mapCenterX;
7146     left = origLeft-offsetX*this.pixPerX ;
7147   }
7148   
7149   if(origTop==divTop)
7150     top = divTop;
7151   else
7152   {
7153     var offsetY = (origTop-divTop)/this.pixPerY ;
7154     var ttb = (origTop < divTop) ;
7155     
7156     var csMinY = this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.minY;
7157     var csMaxY = this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.maxY;
7158     var csCenterY = (this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.minY+this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.maxY)/2;
7159     var csHeight = this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.maxY-this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.minY;
7160     var mapHeight = this.mapWindowMaxLat-this.mapWindowMinLat;
7161     var newCenterY = this.mapCenterY-offsetY ;
7162     var newMapMinY = newCenterY - mapHeight/2 ;
7163     var newMapMaxY = newCenterY + mapHeight/2 ;
7164     if(!ttb)
7165     {
7166       if(newMapMinY < csMinY)
7167       {
7168         if(mapHeight > csHeight)
7169         {
7170           if(newCenterY < csCenterY)
7171             newCenterY = csCenterY ;
7172         }
7173         else
7174         {
7175           if(this.mapWindowMinLat < csMinY)
7176             newCenterY = this.mapCenterY ;
7177           else
7178             newCenterY = newCenterY - (newMapMinY-csMinY) ;
7179         }
7180       }
7181     } 
7182     else
7183     {
7184       if(newMapMaxY > csMaxY)
7185       {
7186         if(mapHeight > csHeight)
7187         {
7188           if(newCenterY > csCenterY)
7189             newCenterY = csCenterY ;
7190         }
7191         else
7192         {
7193           if(this.mapWindowMaxLat > csMaxY)
7194             newCenterY = this.mapCenterY ;
7195           else
7196             newCenterY = newCenterY - (newMapMaxY-csMaxY) ;
7197         }
7198       }
7199     }
7200     offsetY = newCenterY - this.mapCenterY;
7201     top = origTop+offsetY*this.pixPerY ;
7202   }
7203   return {left:Math.round(left), top:Math.round(top)};
7204 }
7205 /**@private 
7206   This function checks the map center to see whether the map goes beyond 
7207   CS boundary. If so, adjust the map center to make sure the map lies
7208   within the cs boundary. This function is called when the map is recentered
7209   or being zoomed.
7210 */
7211 MVMapView.prototype.checkMapCenter = function(center)
7212 {
7213   if (this.overview)
7214     this.reCenterTag = false;
7215   
7216   if(this.wraparound || this.overview || !this.enforceCSBound)
7217     return center;
7218   
7219   if(this.originalCenter == null)
7220     this.originalCenter = center;
7221 
7222   if(this.reCenterTag)
7223     this.originalCenter = center;
7224   else
7225     center = this.originalCenter;
7226 
7227   this.reCenterTag = false;    
7228   
7229   var csMinX = this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.minX;
7230   var csMaxX = this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.maxX;
7231   var csCenterX = (this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.minX+this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.maxX)/2;
7232   var csWidth = this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.maxX-this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.minX;
7233   var mapWidth = this.getPaneWidth()/this.pixPerX ;
7234   var newCenterX = center.getPointX() ;
7235   var newMapMinX = newCenterX - mapWidth/2 ;
7236   var newMapMaxX = newCenterX + mapWidth/2 ;
7237 
7238   if(mapWidth > csWidth)  
7239     newCenterX = csCenterX ;
7240   else
7241   {
7242     if(newMapMinX < csMinX)
7243       newCenterX = csMinX + mapWidth/2 ;
7244     else if(newMapMaxX > csMaxX)
7245       newCenterX = csMaxX - mapWidth/2 ;
7246   }
7247   
7248   var csMinY = this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.minY;
7249   var csMaxY = this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.maxY;
7250   var csCenterY = (this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.minY+this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.maxY)/2;
7251   var csHeight = this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.maxY-this.msi.mapConfig.coordSys.minY;
7252   var mapHeight = this.getPaneHeight()/this.pixPerY ;
7253   var newCenterY = center.getPointY() ;
7254   var newMapMinY = newCenterY - mapHeight/2 ;
7255   var newMapMaxY = newCenterY + mapHeight/2 ;
7256 
7257   if(mapHeight > csHeight)  
7258     newCenterY = csCenterY ;
7259   else
7260   {
7261     if(newMapMinY < csMinY)
7262       newCenterY = csMinY + mapHeight/2 ;
7263     else if(newMapMaxY > csMaxY)
7264       newCenterY = csMaxY - mapHeight/2 ;
7265   }
7266   
7267   return MVSdoGeometry.createPoint(newCenterX, newCenterY, this.srid) ;
7268   
7269 }
7270 /**@private
7271   This function returns the first/bottom native tile layer. A native tile layer
7272   is a tile layer that is defined with a mapviewer instance, not a custom tile layer
7273   or built-in external tile layer.
7274 */
7275 MVMapView.prototype.get1stNativeTileLayer = function()
7276 {
7277   for(var i=0; i<this.mapLayers.length; i++)
7278   {
7279     if(this.mapLayers[i].layerControl)
7280       return this.mapLayers[i].layerControl ;
7281   }
7282   return null ;
7283 }
7284 /**@private
7285   This function combines tile layers that can be rendered as one on the server side. 
7286 */
7287 MVMapView.prototype.combineTileLayers = function()
7288 {
7289   for(var i=0; i<this.mapLayers.length; i++)
7290   {
7291     if(this.mapLayers[i].layerControl)
7292     {
7293       for(var j=i+1; j<this.mapLayers.length; j++)
7294       {
7295         if(MVUtil.canBeCombined(this.mapLayers[i], this.mapLayers[j]))
7296         {
7297           if(!this.mapLayers[i].childrenLayers) // i is a combined layer
7298           {
7299             // need to create a combined layer and replace i with it. 
7300             var combinedLayer = this.mapLayers[i].clone() ;
7301             var  layerControl= new MVMapTilesControl(this, combinedLayer);
7302             combinedLayer.parent = this ;
7303             combinedLayer.layerControl = layerControl ;
7304             combinedLayer.childrenLayers = new Array();
7305             combinedLayer.childrenLayers.push(this.mapLayers[i]) ;
7306             this.mapLayers[i].destroy() ;
7307             this.mapLayers[i].parentLayer = combinedLayer ;
7308             this.mapLayers[i] = combinedLayer ;
7309           }
7310           this.mapLayers[i].childrenLayers.push(this.mapLayers[j]) ;
7311           this.mapLayers[i].isTransparent = this.mapLayers[i].isTransparent && this.mapLayers[j].isTransparent;
7312           this.mapLayers[j].destroy() ;
7313           this.mapLayers[j].parentLayer = this.mapLayers[i] ;
7314           this.mapLayers.splice(j,1) ;
7315           if(this.displayed)
7316             this.mapLayers[i].refresh(true); 
7317         }
7318         else
7319           break ;
7320       }
7321     }
7322   }
7323 }
7324 /**@private
7325   This function combines tile layers that can be rendered as one on the server side. 
7326 */
7327 MVMapView.prototype.tileLayersConfigLoaded = function()
7328 {
7329   for(var i=0; i<this.mapLayers.length; i++)
7330   {
7331     if(!this.mapLayers[i].config)
7332       return false ;
7333   }
7334   return true ;
7335 }

7362 /**
7363   This method adds a MVFOIGroup object to the MVMapView instance. All user defined FOI({@link MVFOI})
7364   objects that belong to the MVFOIGroup object will be added and displayed on the map.
7365   
7366   @param {Object} group a FOI group object 
7367   @returns   None
7368   @type void
7369 */
7370 MVMapView.prototype.addFOIGroup = function (group) 
7371 {
7372   if (this.foiGroupArray == null)
7373     this.foiGroupArray = new Array();
7374   this.foiGroupArray.push(group);
7375   group.parent = this;
7376   if (this.foiGroupLayer == null)
7377      this.createFOIGroupLayer();
7378   group.init(this.foiGroupArray.length - 1);
7379   if (this.displayed)
7380   {
7381     var xOffset = (group.getLayerWidth() - this.getPaneWidth()) * 0.5 / this.pixPerX;
7382     var yOffset = (group.getLayerHeight() - this.getPaneHeight()) * 0.5 /this.pixPerY;
7383     group.setLayerPoistion((this.getPaneWidth()  - group.getLayerWidth())/2,
7384                            (this.getPaneHeight() - group.getLayerHeight())/2);
7385     group.display(this.mapWindowMinLon - xOffset, 
7386                   this.mapWindowMinLat - yOffset, this.mapWindowMaxLon + xOffset, 
7387                   this.mapWindowMaxLat + yOffset, true);
7388   }
7389 }
7390 /**
7391  @private
7392  */
7393 MVMapView.prototype.refreshGroupFOIs = function(initial)
7394 {
7395  this.do_GetMinMaxLonLat();
7396  if (this.foiGroupArray != null)
7397  {
7398    for(var i=0; i<this.foiGroupArray.length; i++)
7399    {
7400      var group = this.foiGroupArray[i];
7401      var xOffset = (group.getLayerWidth() - this.getPaneWidth()) * 0.5 / this.pixPerX;
7402      var yOffset = (group.getLayerHeight() - this.getPaneHeight()) * 0.5 /this.pixPerY;
7403      group.setLayerPoistion((this.getPaneWidth()  - group.getLayerWidth())/2,
7404                             (this.getPaneHeight() - group.getLayerHeight())/2);
7405      
7406      group.display(this.mapWindowMinLon - xOffset, 
7407                   this.mapWindowMinLat - yOffset, this.mapWindowMaxLon + xOffset, 
7408                   this.mapWindowMaxLat + yOffset, initial);
7409    }
7410  }
7411 }

7437 /**
7438  @private
7439  */
7440 MVMapView.prototype.showOverLayerMarkWindow = function(point, domDiv, width, height)
7441 {
7442   if(this.infoWindowTimeout2)
7443   {
7444    clearTimeout(this.infoWindowTimeout2) ;
7445    this.infoWindowTimeout2 = null ;
7446   }
7447   var mv = this ;
7448   var callBack = function(newPoint)
7449   {
7450     if(newPoint)
7451      point = newPoint ;
7452     mv.overlayMarker = true;
7453     mv.infoLayer2.domDiv = domDiv;
7454     if (width == null)
7455       width = 0;
7456     if (height == null)
7457       height = 0;
7458     mv.infoLayer2.showHtmlWindow("",  point.sdo_point.x, point.sdo_point.y, width, height, "MVInfoWindowStyle4");
7459     mv.overlayMarker = false;
7460     mv.infoLayer2.domDiv = null;
7461   }
7462   var showInfoWindow = function()
7463   {
7464     if(mv.displayed)
7465     {
7466       if (!point.srid)
7467         point.srid = mv.srid ;
7468       if (point.srid && (mv.srid != point.srid))
7469         center = mv.transformGeom(point, mv.srid, null, callBack);
7470       else
7471         callBack() ;
7472     }
7473     else
7474       mv.infoWindowTimeout2 = setTimeout(showInfoWindow, 200) ;
7475   }
7476   showInfoWindow() ;
7477 }

7480 {
7481   if (this.infoLayer2.infoWindows.length > 0)
7482     this.infoLayer2.deleteInfoWindow(this.infoLayer2.infoWindows[0]); 
7483 }

7566 /**@private
7567 This method sets how the map should react to touch gestures. It is effective only on 
7568 device that support touch gestures. Currently Oracle Maps only supports touch gestures on 
7569 Apple iOS device. 
7570 
7571 <p>Generally you don't need to make special adjustment to make your Oracle Maps application work
7572 on touch enabled device. You can drag the map by swiping a finger on the map. You can 
7573 zoom the map by pinching two fingers on the map. Touch gestures are mapped to equivalent 
7574 mouse events. So your mouse event listeners will work with touch gestures.</p> 
7575 
7576 <p>By default, tap is equivalent to mouse click, double tap is equivalent to mouse double click, 
7577 single finger swipe is equivalent to mouse drag, tap and hold is equivalent to mouse right click.</p> 
7578  
7579 <p>You can use this method to change the default touch gesture behavior. The touch gesture 
7580 behavior is specified by an object. Each property of the object specifies the behavior of 
7581 a touch gesture. The name of the property is the name of the mouse gesture and the value of
7582 the property is the desired behavior. Currently you set the be behavior of the following
7583 touch gesture(s).</p>
7584 
7585  <table border="1">
7586  <tbody>
7587    <tr>
7588      <th>Gesture</th>
7589      <th>Property name</th>
7590      <th>Value</th>
7591    </tr>
7592    <tr>
7593      <td>Touch and hold
7594      </td>
7595      <td>touchHold
7596      </td>
7597      <td>
7598        <ul>
7599          <li>"do_nothing": Ignore such gesture. 
7600          <li>"mouse_right_click". This is the default behavior. Mouse right click listeners are fired when such gesture occurs.
7601          <li>"mouse_over". Mouse over listeners are fired when such gesture occurs.
7602        </ul> 
7603      </td>
7604    </tr>
7605  </tbody>
7606  </table>
7607 
7608 Example: 
7609 <pre>
7610 mapview.setTouchBehavior({touchHold: "do_nothing"}) ;
7611 </pre>
7612  
7613 @param {Object} behavior An object that specifies the touch gesture behavior.
7614 @returns None   
7615 @type void
7616 */
7617 MVMapView.prototype.setTouchBehavior = function(behavior)
7618 {
7619   this.touchBehavior = behavior ; 
7620 }
7621 /**@private*/
7622 MVMapView.prototype.showCopyRight = function(copyright, options)
7623 {
7624   if ( this.copyright != undefined )
7625   {
7626     this.base_div.removeChild( this.copyright );
7627     delete this.copyright;
7628   }
7629   var left=1 ;
7630   var top=1 ;
7631   var xOffset=0 ;
7632   var yOffset=0 ;
7633   var style=null ;
7634   if(options)
7635   {
7636     if(options.left!=undefined || options.top!=undefined)
7637     {
7638       this.copyrightAutoAdjust = false ;
7639       if(options.left!=undefined)
7640         left = options.left;
7641       if(options.top!=undefined)
7642         top = options.top;
7643       if(options.xOffset!=undefined)
7644         xOffset = options.xOffset;
7645       if(options.yOffset!=undefined)
7646         yOffset = options.yOffset;
7647       if(options.style!=undefined)
7648         style = options.style;
7649     }
7650   }
7651   if(style==null)
7652     style = 'position:absolute;z-index:2000;font-size:12' ;
7653   var spanStr = "<div class=MV_COPYRIGHT style='"+style+"'>";
7654   if(!this.copyrightAutoAdjust)
7655   {
7656     cr = new MVMapDecoration(spanStr+copyright+"</div>", left, top, 500, null, xOffset, yOffset) ;
7657     this.addMapDecoration(cr) ;
7658   }
7659   else
7660   {
7661     var span = document.createElement( "SPAN" );
7662     span.className = "MV_COPYRIGHT" ;
7663     span.innerHTML = " " + copyright + " ";
7664     span.setAttribute("style", style) ;
7665     span.style.cssText = style ;
7666     span.style.position = "absolute";
7667     /*if(this.overviewmap && this.overviewmap.mapDec && !this.overviewmap.mapDec.collapsed)
7668       span.style.right = MVUtil.pixel(this.overviewmap.mapDec.width+3);
7669     else
7670       span.style.right = MVUtil.pixel(this.toolBarContainer.offsetWidth+5);*/
7671     span.style.bottom = MVUtil.pixel(1);
7672     this.base_div.appendChild(span);
7673     this.copyright = span;
7674     this.adjustCopyrightPosition() ;
7675   }
7676 }
7677 /**@private*/
7678 MVMapView.prototype.showEmbeddedCopyright = function()
7679 {
7680   if(this.userDefinedCopyright!=null || this.overview)
7681     return ;
7682   var copyright = this.getEmbeddedCopyright() ;
7683   if(copyright==null)
7684     return ;
7685   this.showCopyRight(copyright) ;
7686 }
7687 /**@private*/
7688 MVMapView.prototype.getEmbeddedCopyright = function()
7689 {
7690   var copyright = "" ;
7691   for(var i=0; i<this.mapLayers.length; i++)
7692   {
7693     var layer = this.mapLayers[i] ;
7694     if(layer.isVisible() && layer.config && layer.config.copyright)
7695     {
7696       if(copyright)
7697         copyright += "; " + layer.config.copyright ;
7698       else
7699         copyright = layer.config.copyright ;
7700     }
7701   }
7702   return copyright ;
7703 }
7704 /**@private*/
7705 MVMapView.prototype.adjustCopyrightPosition = function(mv)
7706 {
7707   if(mv==undefined)
7708     mv = this ;
7709   if(mv==undefined || !mv.copyrightAutoAdjust || !mv.copyright)
7710     return ;
7711   if(this.mapDecorationArray!=null)
7712   {
7713     for(var i=0; i<this.mapDecorationArray.length; i++)
7714     {
7715       var dec = this.mapDecorationArray[i] ;
7716       if(dec.shouldAdjustCopyright && dec.visible && !dec.collapsed)
7717       {
7718         mv.copyright.style.right = MVUtil.pixel(dec.width+3);
7719         return ;
7720       }
7721     }
7722   }
7723   if(mv.overviewmap && mv.overviewmap.mapDec && !mv.overviewmap.mapDec.collapsed && mv.overviewmap.mapDec.visible)
7724     mv.copyright.style.right = MVUtil.pixel(mv.overviewmap.mapDec.width+3);
7725   else
7726     mv.copyright.style.right = MVUtil.pixel(mv.toolBarContainer.offsetWidth+5);
7727 }

7729 /**@private*/
7730 MVMapView.prototype.setTileLayerCursor = function(cursor)
7731 {
7732   if(this.mapLayers)
7733   {
7734     for(var i=0;i<this.mapLayers.length;i++)
7735     {
7736       if (this.mapLayers[i].layerControl)
7737         MVUtil.setCursor(this.mapLayers[i].layerControl.mapLayer,cursor);
7738       else if (this.mapLayers[i].isExtAPITileLayer())
7739         MVUtil.setCursor(this.mapLayers[i].layerDiv.parentNode,cursor);
7740     }
7741   }
7742   if(this.themelayers)
7743   {
7744     for(var i=0; i<this.themelayers.length;i++)
7745     {
7746       if (this.themelayers[i].layerControl)
7747         MVUtil.setCursor(this.themelayers[i].layerControl.mapLayer,cursor);
7748     }
7749   }
7750   if(this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup)
7751   {
7752     for(var i=0; i<this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup.length;i++)
7753     {
7754       if (this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup[i].transImageLayerMap && this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup[i].div)
7755       {
7756         MVUtil.setCursor(this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup[i].div, cursor);
7757       }
7758     }
7759   }
7760 }
7761 /**@private
7762  * Check whether the tile layer is a server side defined builtin external
7763  * tile layer. If it is, create the corresponding builtin tile layer instance
7764  * and add it to the map.
7765  **/
7766 MVMapView.prototype.getTileLayerControl = function(mapTileLayer)
7767 {
7768   if(mapTileLayer.config.clientTileAccess)
7769   {
7770     var ca = mapTileLayer.config.clientTileAccess ;
7771     var tileLayer = null ;
7772     // Add key value to library URL if it is required
7773     if(ca.lib_url && ca.key)
7774       ca.lib_url = ca.lib_url.replace("=$$key$$", "="+ca.key) ;
7775     var options = {key:ca.key, libURL:ca.lib_url} ;
7776     if(ca.type=="google")
7777       tileLayer = new MVGoogleTileLayer(options) ;
7778     else if(ca.type=="bing")
7779       tileLayer = new MVBingTileLayer(options) ;
7780     else if(ca.type=="yahoo")
7781       tileLayer = new MVYahooTileLayer(options) ;
7782     if(tileLayer)
7783     {
7784       tileLayer.setKey(ca.key) ;
7785       if(mapTileLayer.mapType)
7786         tileLayer.setMapType(mapTileLayer.mapType) ;
7787       this.removeMapTileLayer(mapTileLayer) ;
7788       this.addMapTileLayer(tileLayer) ;
7789       return tileLayer ;
7790     }
7791   }
7792   return new MVMapTilesControl(this, mapTileLayer);
7793 }
7794 /**@private*/
7795 MVMapView.prototype.setFOILayersSize = function()
7796 {
7797   for (lc = 0; lc < this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup.length; lc++)
7798   {
7799     this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup[lc].setSize(
7800     parseInt(this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup[lc].themebasedfoi.sizeXratio * (this.getPaneWidth())), 
7801     parseInt(this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup[lc].themebasedfoi.sizeYratio *(this.getPaneHeight())));     
7802   }   
7803   //set the size of individual layer
7804   this.indFOIsControl.setSize(Math.ceil(2 * (this.getPaneWidth())), 
7805                          Math.ceil(2*(this.getPaneHeight())));
7806   if (this.foiGroupArray != null)
7807   {
7808     for(var i=0; i<this.foiGroupArray.length; i++)
7809     {
7810       this.foiGroupArray[i].setSize(Math.ceil(2 * (this.getPaneWidth())), 
7811                                     Math.ceil(2*(this.getPaneHeight())));
7812     }
7813   }
7814 }
7815 /**@private*/
7816 MVMapView.prototype.shouldPinchZoom = function(scale)
7817 {
7818   if(scale==1 || scale<=0)
7819     return false ;
7820   var zoomLevel = this.zoomLevel;
7821   if(scale>1 && zoomLevel < this.maxZoom)
7822     return true ;
7823   else if(scale<1 && zoomLevel>0)
7824     return true ;
7825   else
7826     return false ;
7827 }
7828 /**@private*/
7829 MVMapView.prototype.getPinchZoomingLevel = function(scale)
7830 {
7831   var zoomLevel = this.zoomLevel;
7832   if(scale>0 && (scale<1 && scale>0.9 || scale>1 && scale<1.1))
7833     return zoomLevel ;
7834   var newZoomLevel = zoomLevel;
7835   var maxZoomLevel = this.maxZoom;
7836   var lw = this.msi.getTileWidth(zoomLevel) ;
7837   var targetW = lw / scale ; 
7838   
7839   if(scale<1)
7840   {
7841     // zoom out
7842     newZoomLevel-- ;
7843     for (var i=zoomLevel-1; i>=0; --i)
7844     {
7845       var w = this.msi.getTileWidth(i) ;
7846       if(targetW > w)
7847       {
7848         newZoomLevel = i ;
7849         lw = w ;
7850       } 
7851       else
7852       {
7853         var tmp1 = targetW/lw ;
7854         var tmp2 = w/targetW ; 
7855         if( tmp1 > tmp2 )
7856           newZoomLevel = i;
7857         break ;
7858       }
7859     }
7860   }
7861   else if(scale>1)
7862   {
7863     newZoomLevel++ ;
7864     // zoom in
7865     for (var i=zoomLevel+1; i<=maxZoomLevel; i++)
7866     {
7867       var w = this.msi.getTileWidth(i) ;
7868       if(targetW < w)
7869       {
7870         newZoomLevel = i ;
7871         lw = w ;
7872       } 
7873       else
7874       {
7875         var tmp1 = lw/targetW;
7876         var tmp2 = targetW/w;
7877         if(tmp1 > tmp2)
7878           newZoomLevel = i;
7879         break ;
7880       }
7881     }
7882   }
7883   return newZoomLevel ;
7884 }
7885 /**@private*/
7886 MVMapView.prototype.setTouchCount = function(event)
7887 {
7888   if(event.type=="touchstart")
7889     this.touchCount = event.touches.length ;
7890   else if(event.type=="touchend")
7891     this.touchCount -= event.changedTouches.length ;
7892 }
7893 /**@private*/
7894 MVMapView.prototype.touchStart = function(event)
7895 {
7896   this.setTouchCount(event) ;
7897   if(MVGlobalVariables.isIOS)
7898   {
7899     if(event.touches.length>2)
7900     {
7901       this.cancelTouchAndHold() ;
7902       return ;
7903     }
7904     
7905     this.pinchZoomScale = 1 ;
7906     if(event.touches.length==1)
7907     {
7908       var loc = MVUtil.getMouseXY(event.touches[0]) ;
7909       this.touchStartLocs.push(loc) ;
7910 
7911       // start touch and hold timer
7912       var mv = this ;
7913       var checkTapHold = function()
7914       {
7915         mv.tapHoldTimeOut = null ;
7916         mv.touchAndHold(event) ;
7917         mv.tapHoldFired = true ;
7918       }
7919       this.tapHoldTimeOut = setTimeout(checkTapHold, MVGlobalVariables.touchHoldTimeOut) ;
7920     }
7921     else if(event.touches.length==2)
7922     {
7923       this.cancelTouchAndHold() ;
7924       if(event.changedTouches.length==1)
7925       {
7926         var loc = MVUtil.getMouseXY(event.changedTouches[0]) ;
7927         this.touchStartLocs.push(loc) ;
7928       }
7929       else if(event.changedTouches.length==2)
7930       {
7931         var loc = MVUtil.getMouseXY(event.changedTouches[0]) ;
7932         this.touchStartLocs.push(loc) ;
7933         loc = MVUtil.getMouseXY(event.changedTouches[1]) ;
7934         this.touchStartLocs.push(loc) ;
7935       }
7936     }
7937     if(this.touchStartLocs.length==2)
7938     {
7939       var ox = this.touchStartLocs[1].x - this.touchStartLocs[0].x ;
7940       var oy = this.touchStartLocs[1].y - this.touchStartLocs[0].y ;
7941       this.pinchZoomStartDist = Math.sqrt(ox*ox + oy*oy) ;
7942     }
7943   }
7944 }
7945 /**@private*/
7946 MVMapView.prototype.touchMove = function(event)
7947 {
7948   if(MVGlobalVariables.isIOS)
7949   {
7950     if(event.touches.length==2)
7951     {
7952       var loc1 = MVUtil.getMouseXY(event.touches[0]) ;
7953       var loc2 = MVUtil.getMouseXY(event.touches[1]) ;
7954       var ox = loc1.x - loc2.x ;
7955       var oy = loc1.y - loc2.y ;
7956       var dist = Math.sqrt(ox*ox + oy*oy) ;
7957       this.pinchZoomScale = dist/this.pinchZoomStartDist ;
7958     }
7959   }
7960 }
7961 /**@private*/
7962 MVMapView.prototype.touchEnd = function(event)
7963 {
7964   MVUtil.runListeners(this.EventListeners,MVEvent.MOUSE_UP,[MVUtil.getEvent(event)]);
7965   
7966   if(this.tapHoldFired)
7967   {
7968     this.cancelTouchAndHold();
7969     return ;
7970   }
7971   
7972   var fireClickListener = false ;
7973   if(this.tapHoldTimeOut)
7974     fireClickListener = true ;
7975 
7976   this.cancelTouchAndHold();
7977 
7978   this.touchStartLocs.length = 0 ;
7979   this.setTouchCount(event) ;
7980   if(fireClickListener)
7981   {
7982     if (this.mouseclickListener)
7983     {
7984       this.mouseclickListener(MVUtil.getEvent(event));
7985     }
7986     MVUtil.runListeners(this.EventListeners,MVEvent.MOUSE_CLICK,[MVUtil.getEvent(event)]);
7987   }
7988 }
7989 /**@private*/
7990 MVMapView.prototype.cancelTouchAndHold = function(event)
7991 {
7992   this.tapHoldFired = false ;
7993   if(this.tapHoldTimeOut)
7994   {
7995     clearTimeout(this.tapHoldTimeOut);
7996     this.tapHoldTimeOut = null ;
7997   }
7998   
7999   this.indFOIsControl.cancelTouchAndHold();
8000   for (var lc = 0; lc < this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup.length; lc++)
8001   {
8002     var layer = this.ThemeBasedFOIGroup[lc];
8003     layer.cancelTouchAndHold() ;
8004   }
8005 }
8006 /**@private*/
8007 MVMapView.prototype.touchAndHold = function(evt)
8008 {
8009   if(!this.touchBehavior || !this.touchBehavior.touchHold || 
8010       this.touchBehavior.touchHold == "mouse_right_click")
8011   {
8012     if (this.rightclickListener)
8013     {
8014       this.rightclickListener(MVUtil.getEvent(evt));
8015     }
8016     MVUtil.runListeners(this.EventListeners,MVEvent.MOUSE_RIGHT_CLICK,[MVUtil.getEvent(evt)]);
8017   }
8018 }
8019 
8020 /**
8021  * 
8022  * A global Array variable that specifies functions that are invoked by 
8023  * the Oracle Maps client right after the map is initialized. The Oracle Maps 
8024  * client instance, the MVMapView object, is passed as a parameter to every 
8025  * function specified in MVMapInitializers. 
8026  * 
8027  * <p>A function specified in MVMapInitializers is similar to a MVEvent.INITIALIZE 
8028  * listener function registered with {@link MVMapView#attachEventListener}. 
8029  * The only difference is the way how the function is registered with the Oracle 
8030  * Maps client.</p> 
8031  * 
8032  * <p>The MVEvent.INITIALIZE listener function is registered with {@link MVMapView#attachEventListener}. 
8033  * The function specified in MVMapInitializers is registered by simply adding the
8034  * function to the MVMapInitializers array after the function is defined. 
8035  * Of course the code that defines the function and adds the function to 
8036  * MVMapInitializers needs to be loaded to the page where the map is displayed.</p>
8037  * 
8038  * Example:
8039  * 
8040  * <pre>
8041  *   function myPlugin(mapview)
8042  *   {
8043  *     // do something with the mapview object.
8044  *     ...
8045  *   }
8046  *   
8047  *   // Depending on the order in which scripts are loaded into the application web 
8048  *   // page, it's possible that this piece of code is executed before the Oracle Maps 
8049  *   // library is loaded. So it's important to first check whether MVMapInitializers 
8050  *   // already has been defined and define it if necessary. 
8051  *   var MVMapInitializers = MVMapInitializers || new Array() ;
8052  *   MVMapInitializers.push(myPlugin) ;
8053  * </pre>
8054  *
8055  * @field
8056  */
8057 var MVMapInitializers = MVMapInitializers || new Array() ;
8058
